title: drop dumplings
directions: Mix all together and drop from teaspoon into hot chicken or beef broth.

title: stuffed bass
directions: Dry fish and sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper.
Place fish in a well-greased baking dish.
Melt butter in an iron skillet and saute onion and celery.
Remove from heat; add bread crumbs, bread, egg and seasonings.
Add 2 tablespoons white wine Worcestershire sauce if dry.
Mix thoroughly.
Stuff center of fish with bread stuffing.
Brush with melted butter.
Garnish with thinly sliced bell pepper and lemon twist.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: honey-date muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 6 large or 8 medium muffin cups. Combine muffin mix and dates in a bowl.
Add milk and honey; stir just until blended.
Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 muffins.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Place alternate layers of cabbage, onion and green pepper in a glass bowl. Sprinkle with sugar.
Heat the oil, vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and salt to boiling.
Pour hot mixture over the cabbage, onion and bell pepper.
Let stand in refrigerator for at least 4 hours (24 hours is better).

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat egg whites until they form stiff peaks, gradually adding cream of tartar and sugar.
They will be meringue consistency.
Fold in pecans and chocolate chips. Slightly grease cookie sheet and drop mix by teaspoonfuls onto sheet.
Turn off oven and forget.
Do not make on a rainy day! Makes 5 dozen.

title: turkey wings to the extreme
directions: Boil turkey wings with seasonings for 45 minutes.
Place turkey wings in a pan.
Add Maurice's Meat Sauce.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix cake mix and oil together in a large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add can of Mandarin oranges and mix.
Pour into well greased and floured pans (round). Bake at 350° for the length of time given on the cake box.
This makes 2 or 3 layers, depending on size of pan.

title: cobbler pastry
directions: Combine fruit, sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour onto fruit mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Mix a little flour, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon and a little butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake 5 more minutes.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Put 3 teaspoons butter in baking dish and put in oven until butter melts, then put chicken in dish, skin side down, to coat. When coated, turn over, skin side up, and sprinkle with garlic salt. Bake 1/2 hour, uncovered, at 400°.

title: peach roll-ups
directions: Simmer 1/4 cup butter, sugar, orange juice and orange rind 5 minutes.
Pour half in a 9-inch square pan.
Stir milk into biscuit mix.
Roll out in a 9 x 14-inch rectangle.
Brush with the melted butter. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Arrange drained, sliced peaches over rolled out dough. Roll dough from short side. Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in hot syrup.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Pour remaining syrup over rolls. Continue baking 10 minutes longer.
Serve warm with cream.
Makes 9 servings.

title: apple fritter rings
directions: In bowl, beat egg, milk and 1 teaspoon vegetable oil.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture until smooth (batter will be thick).
Peel, core and slice apples into 1/2-inch slice rings.
In electric skillet or deep fryer, heat oil to 375°.
Dip apple rings into batter; fry few at a time.
Drain on paper towels.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon. Sprinkle over fritters.
Serve warm.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bone; chop by hand.
Add chicken broth; stir well.
Add chopped eggs, chopped pickles, salt and pepper.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate if not used immediately.
May be used for sandwiches or served on lettuce with tomato slices and crackers.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: Dice bananas and apples.
Drain pineapple juice; reserve this. Make jello using 2 cups of hot water and 1 1/2 cups of cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened, then add bananas, apples and pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: scone bread
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease an 8-inch round pan.
Combine first four ingredients and then "cut" in butter with fork until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk, eggs and the raisins.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pat half of dough (with floured hands) into greased pan and add jam (of choice).
Top with remaining dough evenly.
Score dough into 8 wedges and top with melted butter and sugar.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 (8 or 9-inch) cake pans. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces; rinse and pat dry.
Combine hoisin sauce, soybean oil, sherry, soy sauce, honey, minced garlic and ginger root in a bowl and mix well.
Add chicken, tossing to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour 1 1/2 cups hot water over oatmeal.
Let stand 10 minutes. Mix rest of the mixture together, then add oatmeal and butter. Put butter in oatmeal so it can melt.

title: fannie's dumplins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and shortening until it reaches the texture of cornmeal.
Make a well in flour; break egg into this and add milk.
Beat in center with beater, then work all flour into liquid with spatula until stiff.
Roll paper thin using lots of flour on board.
Cut into small pieces and drop into boiling broth.
Stir on top only.
Cook 20 minutes.
Test doneness.

title: country fair casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain well.
Combine ground chuck, onion and seasonings in an iron skillet.
Saute until meat is lightly browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain all grease.
Stir in celery soup and let simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in macaroni and remaining ingredients.
Bake in a lightly greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish for 35 minutes at 350°.
This makes 8 servings.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Stir and let set overnight.
Next day, add 1 grated peel.
Add 1 lemon.
Boil about 15 minutes or until thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Layer ingredients, alternating each.
Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours.

title: fried corn bread
directions: You may use more corn meal to make a stiffer batter.
Mix as listed.
Fry on hot griddle.

title: red bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with cheese and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: apple goodies
directions: Mix sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, salt and apples.
Put in bottom of pan; mix together rest of ingredients.
Place on top of apple mixture.
Bake at 325° to 350° until apples are soft.
Serve hot for supper with milk.

title: dream salad
directions: Mix dry Jell-O and sour cream.
Combine pineapple, coconut, oranges and marshmallows.
Fold in Jell-O and sour cream mixture. Allow to stand overnight.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix crushed Oreos and butter.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with ice cream.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Top with Chocolate Sauce and freeze.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening and cut in with knives until blended.
Gradually add enough cold water to make a pastry consistency.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth. Cover and let rest for 5 minutes.
Roll out onto board in a 12 x 15-inch rectangle, 1/8 to 1/16-inch thickness.
Cut into 2 x 3-inch pieces or 3-inch squares.
Cover with wax paper.
Heat oil.
Drop squares, turning 3 or 4 times while frying.
Drain and serve. Serve with honey.

title: concord punch
directions: Combine.
Slowly bring to a boil.
Serve hot.
If too spicy, cut cinnamon back to 1/2 teaspoon.

title: old recipe tomato soup
directions: Boil tomatoes, onions, sugar, parsley, cloves, salt and pepper until vegetables are thoroughly cooked; strain.
Add milk and butter.
Dissolve cornstarch with water and add also.
Boil until slightly thickened.
Serve with tablespoon of whipped cream.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Cut apricots into small dices and pour
boiling
water over them.
Allow to stand while you stir together the flour, wheat germ and salt.
Then cut in the peanut butter
and
butter.
Add the apricots (drained), then combine the egg yolks and molasses.
Stir in with a few swift strokes. Beat
egg whites until stiff, then fold into batter. Spoon mixture into 8 well oiled muffin cups and drizzle honey over the top.
Bake about 15 minutes.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients, except mushroom sauce.
Form into 8 equally long rolls.
Broil 3 inches from source of heat 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Add to mushroom sauce.
Heat 15 minutes and serve.

title: spinach artichoke supreme
directions: In large bowl, mix spinach, cream cheese, 1/4 cup butter, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into buttered 1-quart casserole dish. Arrange artichokes on top.
Coat croutons with remaining 1/4 cup butter and spread over artichokes.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with butter.
Press in the bottom of an 8 x 12 bowl.
Place in the freezer for a few minutes to get hard.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar, and milk together and put on top of crust.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cream cheese mixture. Add Cool Whip on top of the nuts.
Next, add cherry pie filling on top of Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and peppers.
Add the remaining ingredients, then alternate mixture with tortillas in casserole dish.
Top with grated Longhorn cheese.
Bake at 375°
until hot.

title: german fruit cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together flour and spices.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Fold in the preserves, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Cool; top with caramel icing.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Soften butter.
Beat butter and sugars until blended.
Add peanut butter and blend well.
Add egg and vanilla and beat until well mixed.
Add dry ingredients and mix on low until just blended.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend flour, powdered sugar and margarine to crumb stage. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut hot dogs in 3 pieces.
Cut bacon in half.
Wrap 1 piece of bacon around 1 hot dog.
Stick toothpick in it.
Put them all in crock-pot on high for 4 hours.

title: korean spinach salad
directions: Steam
spinach	until
tender (about 3 minutes).
Drain and squeeze
out
as
much water as possible.
Chop coarsely. Combine remaining ingredients and mix with spinach.
May serve hot or cold.
Serves four.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles according to directions on package.
Cook ground beef until done and drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, oregano, garlic powder and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, tablespoon parsley and egg.
Mix well.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Layer bottom of pan with noodles, sauce, cheese mixture and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add 1 cup ketchup and 1 cup water. Mix well. Cook over medium heat until thoroughly heated. Combine 1/2 cup cold water and flour. Stir until well blended. Add dry mustard, chili powder and salt. Mix until smooth. Gradually add to meat mixture while stirring. Cook over low heat, stirring until thick. Spoon over hamburger buns.

title: banana split pie
directions: For crust, mix cracker crumbs and margarine; press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together next three ingredients and spread over the crust.
Top filling with a layer of sliced bananas dipped in lemon juice to prevent turning brown.
Top bananas with drained crushed pineapple.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple. Garnish with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Prepare as directed on box.
Add other ingredients as listed. Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, which has been greased only on the bottom.
Bake in middle shelf of oven at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove foil and continue baking for 30 minutes more.
May sprinkle with grated cheese the last 15 minutes, if desired.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together oatmeal, butter and boiling water and let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Add white sugar, dark brown sugar, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: hot punch
directions: Combine apple cider, lemonade, orange juice, water and sugar in party-sized coffee pot.
Place allspice, cloves, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in basket of coffee pot.
Perk until coffee pot cuts off.
May be made early and warmed.
Yield:
20 servings.

title: kahlua
directions: Use filter and make coffee.
Pour into stainless pot and add 3 cups sugar.
Cool down to 100°.
Add 1 1/2 cups grain alcohol (Everclear) and 1 teaspoon pure vanilla.

title: pumpkin pecan loaves
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. Combine the pumpkin, oil, eggs and water. Mix well. Stir into dry ingredients just until combined. Fold in the pecans.

Spoon into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans to wire racks.

title: cranberry salad mold
directions: Put washed cranberries in blender to grind.
Combine ground cranberries and marshmallows and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight. Next day, add remaining ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spread nuts and then coconut on bottom of dish.
Pour German chocolate cake mix batter over nuts and coconut.
Melt butter; add cream cheese and sugar.
Mix well and spread over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: microwave mexican casserole
directions: Crumble beef, onion and pepper in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover.
Cook on High power 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir; cook 2 1/2 minutes more and drain.
Add the tomatoes, chili beans, taco seasoning and cheese.
Cover and cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir; cook on 80% (reheat power) 5 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle broken taco chips on top.
Leave cover off.
Microwave on 80% (reheat) 1 1/2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes and serve.

title: crisp pastel cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar, shortening, margarine, vanilla, eggs and dry gelatin.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt. Shape dough into 3/4-inch balls.
Place 3 inches apart on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar. Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Yields about 5 dozen cookies.

title: best tomato catsup
directions: Measure spices into saucepan.
Add vinegar and cover.
Heat to a boil, Remove from heat; let stand while you prepare tomato mixture.
(Spices steep in vinegar- just like tea.
It's this separate brewing for spice flavor that keeps catsup a rich red color.)

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for at least 20 minutes or cook in slow cooker for 1 to 2 hours.

title: craig's crazy chili
directions: Brown ground chuck. Using a fork, break meat into small bite sized pieces. Place mix, beans, tomatoes and tomato sauce in a large saucepan. Add browned meat. Simmer over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours to blend flavors.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup pecans and bananas.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on racks. Spread with Cream Cheese Frosting.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup chopped pecans.

title: candied nuts
directions: Mix together in an iron skillet. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until liquid disappears (10 to 15 minutes). Spread out on cookie sheet. Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: instant coffee mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Use 3 rounded teaspoonfuls to 6 ounces water.
May add sugar if needed.
Heat in microwave or use boiling water.

title: coconut-date mounds
directions: Crush cornflakes slightly with hands; set aside.
Combine dates, sugar and eggs in a 10-inch skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture pulls away from the sides of the pan, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir walnuts and vanilla into date mixture.
Gently stir in cornflakes.
Cool slightly, about 5 minutes.
Shape mixture into 1 1/2-inch balls. Roll each in flaked coconut.
Place on waxed paper lined baking sheets.
Press a candied cherry half in each ball, flattening slightly.
Makes 24.

title: effie kennedy's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll and cut.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bombay refresher
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Chill until icy cold.
When serving, add chutney and nuts and sprinkle with coconut.
One tablespoon chutney is usually enough per bowl.
This is a different, very tasty addition to a summer dinner party.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups (4 servings).

title: shrimp rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Combine crumbs, oleo and 6 tablespoons powdered sugar to make crust.
Put in square casserole dish.

title: carolyn's strawberry crunch dessert
directions: Mix the first 4 dry ingredients; stir into melted butter until well blended.
Bake on large cookie sheet set at 350° for 20 minutes.
Stir OFTEN.
Mixture should be crumbly.
Cool.
Can be made ahead and stored in a tightly covered jar until needed.

title: zerger beans
directions: Brown meat and onion, drain.
Drain beans some and add all ingredients to slow cooker.
Cook 2-3 hours.

title: lemon blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatins together in boiling water.
Add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually stir in pie filling.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Chill until firm.
Fold sugar into sour cream just until blended.
Spread over gelatin.

title: canadian cake
directions: Cream
butter
and sugar together.
Add lemon juice and well beaten
eggs.
Add	flour
and baking powder, flavoring, dates and
nuts.	Bake
slowly
3 to 4 hours at 325° to 350°. Cut baking time in half when making half the recipe.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a small saucepan; add curry powder and saute 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in honey, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Place chicken pieces on rack in shallow roasting pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Brush with part of the glaze mixture and bake 15 minutes longer or until tender, brushing frequently with remaining glaze.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy toffee cookie bars
directions: In a large bowl beat butter until fluffy.
Beat in brown sugar; add egg yolk.
Beat in flour and then vanilla.
Spread evenly (as possible) onto greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Shut off oven and remove tray to sprinkle chips evenly over surface.
Return to off oven for at least 5 minutes, then spread smooth chocolate.
Sprinkle top with nuts.
Allow to cool, then score top with knife and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Break into bars.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well. Add milk and mix.
Add dry ingredients alternately with bananas. Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spicy walnut raisin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
With rotary beater, beat remaining ingredients except walnuts and raisins until blended. Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan. Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until filling is set and pastry is nicely browned.
Serve slightly warm or cool.
Great with whipped cream.

title: linda's famous musli
directions: Pour oatmeal into mixing bowl.
Add enough water to cover oatmeal.
Let stand until moisture is taken up.
Drizzle honey over mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and apple.
Serve for breakfast. Apples will turn brown if not served immediately.
Serves 2.

title: beef in wine
directions: Use a good cut of beef (not stew meat).
Dice and mix with remaining ingredients in covered casserole.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.
Serve over buttered noodles or rice.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease Dutch oven lightly.
Pour in fruit.
Spread cake mix on top
and
smooth
out.
Melt margarine and pour evenly over batter.
Cover and bake about 10 minutes and check to see if fruit is
bubbling
through batter.
If it is, remove from fire and leave coals on top until batter is browned.

title: new england fruit bread
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar: add eggs and mashed bananas. Blend thoroughly.
Stir together flour, baking soda:
add to banana mixture.
Blend.
Stir in nuts, chocolate chips and maraschino cherries.
Divide batter into 3 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350 for 1 - 1 1/2 hours.
Check with toothpick.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm buttermilk. Set aside.
Sift soda, salt, sugar and flour in bowl. Cut in shortening. Add yeast mixture. Stir until blended. Knead and roll 1/2 inch thick. Cut out biscuits and dip in melted butter.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together adding chocolate chips last. Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: five hour stew
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Place all ingredients in a large heavy saucepan.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: tuna macaroni casserole
directions: Bring water to a boil and add macaroni.
Cook until tender; drain and add butter, cheese and macaroni into large baking dish (reserve small amount of cheese for top).
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Empty undrained pineapple into
pan.
Add
cherry
pie
filling; mix together. Next sprinkle nuts.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top. Add fruit and nuts
to	cover.	Drop 1/4-inch sliced pieces of stick butter over entire top
of	cake mix.
Bake until top is brown.

title: potato soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl, mixing until completely blended.
Store in airtight container.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Top with catsup.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: white chocolate cheese fruit tart
directions: Cream butter and sugar, then mix in flour.
Press into the bottom of a 12-inch round pan or a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: crazy bread(pan tonto)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except the flour; mix well.
Begin adding 1/2 cup of flour at a time until you have a nice, thick batter (you judge).
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 25 to 35 minutes.
When time is over, turn off oven and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Leave in the oven for 10 additional minutes.
After removed from oven, wait 45 minutes before serving. You may top each piece with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Add bouillon cubes, salt, pepper, Season-All salt and onions while chicken is cooking.
I take the chicken off of the bones and I also use 4 to 6 chicken breasts instead of 1 whole chicken.
Put chicken back in broth.

title: mixed veggies
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet. Add ingredients in skillet along with the garlic and water. Cover and steam for approximately 5 - 8 minutes, depending on personal taste. Serve while hot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Combine with rice, soup and cheese. Mix well. Pour into a casserole dish which has been sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Marinate vegetables and bacon bits in mayonnaise overnight. Before serving, add 2 cups crumbled cornbread.

title: kick-a-pooh juice
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Drink 4 ounces morning and 4 ounces night. Good for arthritis.
Gives you go power.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello in a cup of hot water.
Into this stir marshmallows.
Chill.
When beginning to thicken, add pineapple, nuts, mayonnaise, cream and cream cheese or cottage cheese.
Mold and chill.

title: brown rice
directions: Put little rices in the hamburger stuff.
Put it on your plate and get it hot.

title: zucchini bread with cheese spread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; stir in walnuts and dates. Combine sugars, oil, eggs, milk, vanilla, and zucchini; stir well. Add zucchini mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour batter into 12 greased and floured 1 cup miniature Bundt pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Let cool in pans 5 minutes.
Remove from pans, and let cool on wire racks.
Serve with cheese spread.
Yield:
12 (4 inch) loaves.

title: korean barbecued beef
directions: Cut meat into slices and marinate for 15 to 30 minutes. Larger pieces should be marinated 1 to 2 hours.
Broil over hot charcoals.
Turn meat only once.

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine Jell-O and water.
Bring to a boil.
When cooled, stir in apricots and pineapple.
Combine cream cheese and milk and beat until smooth with electric mixer.
Fold into gelatin mixture and put into mold on dish and refrigerate.
Spray mold with Pam.

title: seven-layer salad
directions: You will also need 1 (9 x 13) glass pan.

title: fat-free pumpkin gingerbread
directions: Combine flour, cornmeal, baking soda, ginger and allspice. Mix well.
Add pumpkin, juice and molasses.
Mix until moist. Fold in raisins, if desired.
Coat 4 (1 pound) cans with nonstick spray.
Divide batter among cans.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set 10 minutes, then remove from cans.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix together the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Beat the eggs, flour and salt for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour in tube pan.
Put in cold oven.
Then turn oven on after you put cake in oven at 300°.
Bake for 1 hour.
Wait 30 minutes before you check the cake for the first time.

title: hurry dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Spray 9 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Spread apple filling in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling. Melt butter and pour over mixture.
Sprinkle walnuts evenly over mixture.
Bake approximately 1 hour or until top is golden brown.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix by hand.
Freeze in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Serve frozen.

title: pineapple mini-pies
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, salt and lemon peel.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender.
Add pineapple juice and mix to form dough.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness and cut rounds 1/2 inch larger than pineapple slice.
Cut 8 this size and, using a donut cutter, cut 8 more.

title: sania (hamburg in the oven)
directions: Mix meat, onions, parsley well and season with the salt and pepper and allspice.
Press into a roasting pan to form a flat loaf about 1-inch thick.
Place in a 350° oven and brown for about 1/2 hour (meat will shrink a little from sides of pan).
While this is browning, brown the potato halves in hot oil in a skillet until they form a crust.
Put aside.

title: orange chocolate delight
directions: Place orange juice and ice cream in blender until smooth. Fill tall glasses 1/2 full of crushed ice. Fill half way with ginger ale.
Add blender mixture and stir gently. Top with a maraschino cherry.
Makes 8 tall glasses.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix well as listed.
Pour into a well-greased cookie sheet or pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° until golden brown and firm in middle (30 to 45 minutes).
Test with toothpick.

title: orange slice pies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.
I use hand mixer for all but oranges.
I fold them in last gently.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream margarine, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs in a mixing bowl on low speed, then on high speed. Scrape bowl. In another bowl, sift the flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together. Add to mixer and mix until blended. Form dough into tablespoon-size balls. Mix 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon in small bowl. Roll cookie dough balls in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Place cookie dough balls 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake just until firm. Does not need to look brown. Carefully lift onto cooling rack to cool completely. Yields 5 dozen.

title: butter nut crunch
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and butter.
Heat to boiling.
Cook to light crack stage, 285°.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Pour into well greased cookie sheet; cool.
Spread half of chocolate over top and sprinkle with 1/2 cup walnuts.
Spread second half chocolate over nuts and then sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Break into pieces to serve.
Makes about 2 dozen pieces.

title: sweet potatoe casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in glass casserole dish. Do not cover. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or till potatoes are tender.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat egg yolks until creamy.
Fold in condensed milk, beat lightly.
Stir in lime juice and zest.
When thickened, pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites until very stiff and peaks form.
Slowly add sugar.
Add vanilla when all the sugar is added.
Spread over pie.
Brown under broiler until meringue is golden.
Chill before serving.

title: dilled green beans
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, boil water, vinegar and dill.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Saute onions in butter until tender.
Stir in green beans, salt and savory.
Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes; stir continuously.

title: chocolate rice krispies squares
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients over low heat until smooth, then remove from heat.
Add 1 cup powdered sugar, vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Put in well greased pan and cool in refrigerator until firm.

title: pistachio bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well. Mix 2 tablespoons sugar, 2 tablespoons cinnamon and 1 teaspoon nutmeg in small bowl.
Grease 3 mini or 2 large loaf pans.
Pour part of dough in each pan; sprinkle half of cinnamon mixture, rest of dough and top with remaining cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: shrimp vinaigrette
directions: In a glass dish, layer shrimp and onions.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Drain shrimp, arrange on plate.
I garnish with fresh chives (chopped) and serve with toothpicks.

title: dip for assorted crackers
directions: Soften cheese, using enough milk to cream well.
Dice the package of beef fine; add and mix in garlic salt to taste.
Good with assorted crackers, pretzels or chips.

title: mexican salad
directions: Steam green beans until tender-crisp, about 15 minutes. Drain.
Whisk together other ingredients and pour over warm green beans.
Allow to marinate at least 1/2 hour.
Serve at room temperature or chilled.
Yield: 4 servings.
Carbohydrate 12 g, protein 3 g, fat 28 g, calories 292.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix all wet ingredients and add to dry, stirring to moisten well.
Cover and store in refrigerator until ready to bake, as long as 5 to 6 weeks.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Thoroughly grease muffin pan cups.
Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Divide each piece into thirds.
Shape into balls.
Place 3 balls in each prepared muffin cup.
Let rise as directed.
Bake for 7 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef; drain.
Add beans, tomato juice and chili powder.
Let mixture come to a boil; add sugar.
Cook 1 hour on medium heat.

title: raisin bread
directions: Set aside milk to cool slightly.
Mix yeast into warm water; melt margarine (or butter) and combine with salt, sugar and egg. Combine all the above ingredients with the flour and milk and mix together lightly with fork or hands.
Let this dough stay in a covered bowl at room temperature for 1 hour.
After 1 hour beat batter down, add raisins and divide dough in half; put in bread pans; place in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour water over oatmeal in a large bowl; cool.
Stir in 2 cups of flour and yeast.
Raise, uncovered, until doubled in bulk. Punch down; work in salt, oil, molasses and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead, adding extra flour is necessary for about 10 minutes.
Divide in 3. Form loaves in 3 buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Allow to rise again until doubled.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 minutes.

title: wimpies(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown meat; add other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Makes a big batch.
You can freeze half for later.
Serve on a roll.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion, and pepper.	Drain and add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 hours.	Add cheese on top of each bowl of soup.

title: powdered sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together. Mix the next 4 dry ingredients together. Add the dry ingredients to the egg mixture. Form into a big smooth ball; chill 15 minutes.
Pinch off into small balls and flatten with a fork or bottom of glass. Bake as usual for cookies at 350° until light brown.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 9 mins. (Do not overbake.) Cookies will be soft.
They will puff while baking and flatten while cooking. Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Cool completely. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: zucchini with pesto
directions: Wash basil leaves thoroughly in lukewarm water and drain well. Add basil and next 3 ingredients to food processor bowl and process until smooth.
Combine water and oil; with processor running, pour oil mixture through food chute in a slow, steady stream until combined.
Set aside.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli, drain and set aside.
Saute onion in oleo; add soup.
Melt cheese in mixture.
Add salt, pepper, Accent, Worcestershire sauce and mushrooms.
Stir in broccoli.
Add almonds.
Serve warm with Fritos, tacos or Melba rounds.

title: easy chili
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together. Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Pour all ingredients into a crock-pot or Dutch oven and cook over low heat for 1 to 2 hours.

title: crab bites
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well. Spread on English muffins and cut into wedges.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
These can be frozen before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries in water 5 minutes. Add sugar. Boil 5 minutes longer. Add Jell-O, pineapple, grapes and nuts. Place in glass dish and refrigerate until chilled.

title: press cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients with Crisco and butter.
Add seed; mix well.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Grease pan; may be chilled.
Bake about 20 minutes until golden brown at 375°.

title: barry's favorite chocolate cake
directions: Heat 1 stick butter in water to boil.
After water and butter have boiled, add 1 cup cold milk, 2 beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add wet ingredients and blend well. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: date nut balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook over low heat 10	minutes.
Add
Rice
Krispies
and nuts.
When cool, shape into balls; roll in coconut.

title: carrot marmalade
directions: Peel the carrots.
Remove seeds from the lemons and put through meat grinder.
Put on to boil with very little water. Cook slowly until tender, then add the sugar and boil until thick.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together with lite Miracle Whip (do not thin). Chill and serve.

title: 22 minute cake
directions: In medium saucepan, bring to boil margarine, cocoa and water. Add to sugar and flour in mixing bowl; blend together.
Add sour milk, baking soda, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes in 12 x 15-inch pan, greased.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, mix nuts, sugar, syrup and salt.
Cook uncovered on high for 4 minutes.
Stir.
Cook on high for 4 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Cook for 2 more minutes on high.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour out on a greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into pieces. Store in air tight container

title: chocolate frosting for texas crude cake
directions: Place margarine in a 4-cup glass measure.
Microwave on High power
30 to 40 seconds or until melted.
Stir in cocoa; then milk.
Blend
in
sugar
and
vanilla
to
make a smooth Frosting. Spread on top of cake in dish.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt the butter, stir in the brown sugar, corn syrup and salt. Stir constantly, bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and vanilla.
It will bubble up.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: salsa
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; taste for hotness before adding jalapenos.
Place in covered container and chill.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Split rolls.
Melt margarine and add mustard, Worcestershire sauce and poppy seed.
Spread mixture evenly on both sides of rolls.
Add small pieces of ham and cheese.
Cook at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pickled garden vegetables
directions: Sprinkle zucchini, beans, onions and pepper lightly with salt; let stand 15 minutes.
Rinse well.
Stir vegetables into boiling water to cover; cook, uncovered, 2 minutes.
Drain; rinse with cold water.

title: buffalo chicken wings
directions: Deep fry or bake chicken.
Melt butter and mix with hot sauce and dressing.
Dip chicken in mixture.
Coats approximately 40 wing pieces.

title: meat and vegetable dish
directions: Cut onions, peppers and sausage in strips.
Heat oil in skillet and fry sausage until brown.
Add onions and peppers and cook all together.
Add green beans, cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook for 15-20 minutes.

title: cranberry nut loaves
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and soda into a large mixing bowl to blend.
Whisk eggs to mix and add melted butter, heated orange juice and grated rind.
Blend and add to dry ingredients.
Mix just enough to blend.
Add cranberries and nuts; mix through.
Bake in 2 medium, well greased loaf pans (fill 2/3 full).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
This freezes well.

title: brownies
directions: Mix butter and sugar in a bowl.
Combine butter mixture with all
other	ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan; bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.	Serves 20.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Cream	butter	 and
sugar.
Add
vanilla.
Add
flour gradually
until
it can be handled without sticking to hands. Add nuts, blending well.
Pinch off dough in small balls.
Put in ungreased pan and cook 40 minutes at 300°.	When cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Fold in sifted flour (save 1/2 cup flour to mix with fruit), cinnamon and soda. Mix well with sugar and butter.
Mix all other ingredients together and stir into first mixture.
Batter should be stiff. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pecan (or walnut) pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, salt, butter and vanilla; add beaten eggs. Pour in a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle nuts over filling. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: barbecue brisket
directions: Combine onion salt, celery salt, garlic powder and liquid smoke.
Rub onto brisket.
Wrap brisket in heavy foil.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Before cooking, remove foil from brisket and cover with Worcestershire sauce.
Rewrap in foil and bake 4 hours in 300° oven.
If there is a lot of juice, drain it off and then pour barbecue sauce over brisket.
Cook one hour longer in 350° oven.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup, mayonnaise and curry powder together and set aside.
In buttered casserole dish spread chicken, then broccoli, then cover with the soup mixture and then the cheese.
Finish with the grated cheese and cover with bread crumbs; dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Heat marshmallows and orange juice in top of a double boiler over simmering water until marshmallows are melted, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat; turn into a bowl.
Let cool.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Slice sugar cookies; place in pizza pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Spread pineapple and bananas over crust.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread over bananas.
Place oranges, kiwi and strawberries.

title: beef enchiladas
directions: Cook and set aside.

title: asparagus and corn casserole
directions: Cook corn until barely tender; drain and reserve liquid.
Melt margarine in saucepan and blend in flour.
Gradually add milk and vegetable liquids (1/2 cup).
Stir until thick and smooth.
Add celery salt.
Layer corn and asparagus in a sprayed casserole. Pour cream sauce over that and top with bran or crumbs and cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: almond wedding punch
directions: Heat sugar and water until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Stir in orange juice, lemonade and pineapple juice.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
May freeze before adding ginger ale.
May also add ice.

title: ting a lings(a candy)
directions: Melt morsels in pan over boiling water.
Remove from heat. Add noodles, nuts and raisins.
Toss gently until blended.
Drop from a teaspoon onto wax paper.
Let harden.
Makes about 36 clusters.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine egg, oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except raisins. Gradually add to zucchini mixture.
Blend.
Stir into raisins. Pour into two loaf pans that have been greased with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: classic hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in green beans, soup, water and seasonings.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In medium bowl combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon mixture in mounds around edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until heated through.
Top potatoes with cheese and remaining onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chop block bread
directions: Mix Jiffy mix according to directions on package.
Add all other ingredients; mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in greased pan.
Turn upside down and allow to cool.

title: creamy basil dressing
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar together until sugar begins to dissolve. Slowly add eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Add spices.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Put graham cracker crust in 9-inch springform pan.
Take 2 (8 ounce) cream cheese and whip until fluffy.
Add milk until smooth. Add 1 egg at a time and whip until fluffy.
Pour in springform pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with cherry pie filling when cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish; add sugar to melted margarine.
Stir in 1 egg at a time; mix well.
Add pineapple and add bread pieces.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: molded pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and chill until partially set.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Put into mold and chill until set.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix together. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350°.

title: cheese clouds
directions: Mix cheese and butter with hands until mixed well, then mix in other ingredients.
Mix with hands for at least 10 minutes, then mix with beater for 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Add salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Bring to boil, dissolving bouillon cubes.
Add noodles.
Cook until almost tender.
Add milk, cheese and broccoli.
Reduce heat slightly.
Cook until broccoli is tender.
Full recipe serves 6 to 8.

title: how to make a birthday special
directions: To have a successful life, you must cultivate your own garden, planting as follows:

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onions and peppers in margarine.
Add flour.
Stir in milk.
Bring to boil and simmer 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add all ingredients, except cheese.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round baking pans.
In a large mixing bowl beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat on medium speed of electric mixer for 1 minute.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon, beef, onions and green peppers until meat is done. Combine remaining ingredients in a large baking dish.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: mock "cream puffs"
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Cut cookies in half.
Place 1 tablespoon of mixture between each cookie half.
Should be refrigerated.

title: peanut butter brown sugar fudge
directions: Cook sugars, butter, milk and salt to softball stage or 234 degrees. Add marshmallows and peanut butter just before removing from heat. Do not stir. Cool to room temperature. Add vanilla; beat until mixture is creamy and thick (mixture sets up quick). Pour into buttered shallow pan. Cut into squares. Yield 2 doz. This recipe can be doubled.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender or food processor.
Place layer of cookies in the bottom of a clean flower pot.
Combine margarine, Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar and layer over cookies. Combine pudding, milk and vanilla; blend until thickened.
Add over first mixture. Continue to alternate layers, putting cookies (dirt) on top.
Use trowel for serving.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Put first 3 ingredients into a mixing bowl.
Add the boiling water.
(I use large electric mixer to mix.)
Mix until melted. Let it cool to warm temperature.
Add the 3 beaten eggs.
Mix yeast with sifted flour and add to mixture in mixing bowl. Continue to beat with mixer until well blended.
Put into a greased bowl.
Cover with wet towel and put into refrigerator until dough rises (takes about 1 hour).
Roll out and cut.
No kneading necessary.
(Let rise again, takes about 30 minutes.) Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: sliced tomatoes and mozzarella with three-herb pesto
directions: On a large round platter, alternate tomato and Mozzarella slices overlapping slightly and spoon pesto in a ring around center of slices.
Sprinkle tomatoes and Mozzarella with pepper and garnish with herbs.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine ingredients and spread in casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and 1 cup crushed potato chips. Bake in a 425° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, until chips are brown.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix all together.
Spread on top of cooked cake.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While still warm, dust with powdered sugar.
When very cool, cut into squares.

title: cheese canape
directions: Mix the oleo and cheese.
Add flour, Rice Krispies and cayenne pepper. Mix well.
Make into balls in the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pat down the bottom of flour-coated glass.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: blackberry jelly
directions: Heat berries in pan and use cream potato masher to crush berries.
Put berries in cloth and squeeze out juice.
Mix 1 cup juice to 1 cup sugar.
Put at least 2 cups juice and 2 cups sugar in pan.
Let it boil rapidly for 15 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes well.
Squeeze out all the juice.
Break artichokes into small pieces and add mayonnaise, parmesan cheese and green chilies.
Mix well.
Add any optional ingredients at this point.
Place in shallow baking dish (one that can be served in) and bake at 350 degrees for approximately 20 minutes or until brown on top.
Blot excessive oil with paper towels.
Serve hot with king size Fritos, Melba toast rounds or other crackers.

title: pudding in a cloud
directions: Spoon 1/3 cup of whipped topping into each of 6 dessert glasses.
Using back of spoon, make depression in center and spread topping up sides of glass.

title: potato casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: four layer chocolate pie
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, oleo and nuts together.
Place in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Stir sugar and cinnamon together. Cut biscuits into halves and then half again and one more time, making 6 pieces to one biscuit. Shake biscuits, one can at a time, in the sugar and cinnamon mixture. Spray Bundt pan with Pam. Put biscuits into Bundt pan. Pour butter into leftover sugar and cinnamon mixture, then pour over the top of the biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cool and turn upside down onto plate.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oven-barbecued pork chops
directions: Place chops in heavy cast-iron skillet.
Combine all remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Separate and cut up broccoli.
Add mushrooms, raisins, onions and bacon and toss.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar and pour over salad.
Let stand several hours or overnight.

title: mousse delight
directions: Use pastry blender, combine first 3 ingredients.
Crumb together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Combine next 3 ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Spread over first layer.
Mix last 2 ingredients and spread over second layer.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: dessert (fruit) pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together like a pie crust. Put into pizza pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes. Cool. Beat next 3 ingredients together until creamy. Spread on cooled crust. Arrange sliced fruit on top of cream cheese mixture. Boil last 3 ingredients together one minute or until thick. Let cool. Pour over fruit. Let stand 1-2 hours before serving.

title: sour cream banana cake
directions: Grease loaf pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Add bananas, nuts and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all liquids.
Add flour.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until done over medium heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add half and half and broth; cook, stirring constantly, until thickens.
Add pimento, parsley, a few almonds and cooked rice.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: billy regan's baked scallops
directions: Mince the onion and garlic.
Crush the crackers.
In a large skillet, melt the butter.
Saute the onion and garlic.
Add the cracker crumbs.
Mix and cook until semi crunchy.
Add the scallops.
Stir together until cooked to desired doneness.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, flour, shortening, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix remaining sugar, margarine and boiling water.
Pour over batter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine corn, salt, pepper, flour and egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into corn mixture.
Drop mixture by tablespoons into hot oil.
Cook until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Melt margarine in Pyrex dish.
Place layers of the other ingredients on top and pour milk over it.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: effie's pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavors.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 300° oven.

title: oriental salad
directions: Pour over first mixture and cover in refrigerator for 3 days. Then put into small jars.
Keep in refrigerator.
Good summer salad!

title: cheddar cheese and macaroni
directions: In saucepan over medium-high heat, melt 1/4 cup margarine. Blend in flour gradually.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to thicken and boil.
Cook and stir 1 minute.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Combine cheese sauce and macaroni in 2-quart casserole.
Melt remaining margarine; stir in cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 7.

title: green and white salad
directions: Chop cauliflower, broccoli, cucumber and spring onions up into small, fine pieces.
Set aside.
Mix together the rest of the ingredients in a large bowl.
Add vegetables and stir. Refrigerate overnight.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 1 tablespoon per cup of boiling water.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick.
Mix egg with salt and pepper. Dip tomatoes into crumbs, then into egg.
Dip into crumbs again. Fry in small amount of oil until browned on both sides.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil fryer or chicken breasts or wings in 2 1/2 to 3-quarts of water to which salt and pepper have been added.
When the chicken is done, debone and set aside.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper in large Dutch oven. Drain.
Return to Dutch oven; add garlic salt and next 4 ingredients.
Stir well; cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni; omit salt.
Add to meat mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top evenly with pepperoni.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Top with cheese and bake uncovered 5 minutes.

title: dakota beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in large skillet.
Mix remaining ingredients in a large (about 3-quart size) casserole dish.
Add hamburger and onion.
Mix again.
Cover.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Line a greased Pyrex with shredded, chipped beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with slice of bacon.
Lay on chipped beef.
Mix sour cream and soup together and pour over chicken.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice.

title: turkey meat loaf
directions: Make into loaf and bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Make glaze.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cream and cinnamon. Peel and slice peaches. Put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken, Doritos, cheese and onions.
Mix in saucepan soups, chicken broth, Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Heat and stir until boiling.
Pour over layered mixture.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly and lightly brown.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and freeze.
When ready to use, add 2 bottles ginger ale.
Other flavor of Kool-Aid may be used also.

title: texas slab cake
directions: Combine water, Crisco and butter in pan; bring to a boil. Pour over sugar and flour. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, vanilla and salt. Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: kathy's crock pot barbecue
directions: Sear the roast on all sides in a little oil before putting in crock pot.
Add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Start crock pot on high for about 1 hour; reduce heat to low and continue cooking for about 10 hours, or until the meat is so tender that it falls apart.
Remove meat from crock pot; discard any bones and fat. Cut meat into small pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients for sauce and toss with meat.
(Discard all unused drippings from the crock pot.
There is too much vinegar in this to use it all.)
Return meat and sauce to crock pot to keep warm during serving. Delicious!

title: rice krispie treats
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and peanut butter in a large pan on stove top.
Do not let it come to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press into nonstick pan or flat Tupperware container with hands.
Cool, then cut into cookies.
Makes about 16 to 20 treats.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar and egg. Sift in all dry ingredients and stir until dough becomes well mixed.
(Self-rising flour can be used and omit baking soda, powder and salt.)
Roll into balls the desired size.
Place 3 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake until set but not hard.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into dish and freeze.
Just before serving remove from freezer and let thaw slightly.

title: fancy strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin
in
hot
water.
Add remaining ingredients, except sour
cream, and stir together well.
Pour half of mixture into 1 1/2
quart
mold
or
8 x 10-inch dish. Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: "cholesterol city" biscuits
directions: Mix and pat out on floured surface 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into 12 biscuits and bake in a 375° oven for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Chop green tomatoes in blender or grind.
Chop apples in blender or grind.
Mix all ingredients together in saucepan. Bring to rapid boil.
Simmer until thickened, from 1 to 2 hours. Makes about 5 cups.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cut carrots into long strips; set aside.
(Can use canned carrots.)
Mix water, salt, brown sugar, oleo and cinnamon into 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Microwave on High until oleo is melted (45 seconds).
Stir to blend.
Stir in carrots until coated.
Cover.
Microwave until carrots are tender, 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir once.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of large casserole that has a lid. Peel potatoes and slice about 1/8-inch thick and arrange over the top of meat.
Drain and rinse sauerkraut and put over top of the potatoes.
Pour wine over top.
Top with a few sprigs of rosemary, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until meat is done and tender and potatoes are tender.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Can use butternut flavoring.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Take one pie crust and sprinkle bottom lightly with sugar and cinnamon.
Pour apple pie filling into crust.
Take some sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over top of filling, as desired.
Cut second pie crust into long strips and place slightly apart on top of pie filling.

title: judy's applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix beef, applesauce and bread crumbs.
Add eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Roll in flour and brown in hot shortening.
Place meatballs in casserole dish, draining off excess fat.

title: bar-b-que
directions: Put meat in slow cooker around mid-morning.
Cook slowly several hours, adding water if needed.
Cook until meat starts to pull apart with fork.
Drain off some of the liquid.
In the meantime, saute celery, onions and green pepper in a little butter.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and simmer.
Add more hot pepper or BBQ sauce to taste.
Then shred meat and mix with sauce and simmer again for about 1 to 2 hours.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together the cake ingredients until well blended.
Pour into sheet pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: spiced nut cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add the orange juice, water, butter and egg; mix until well blended.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Grease and line with wax paper a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Spoon in mixture.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from pan; peel off the paper and dust with powdered sugar. Slice and serve warm or cold with butter or cream cheese.

title: cheese boat
directions: Scoop out center of bread.
Mix remaining ingredients well. Stuff mixture into center of bread.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.

title: four fruit compote
directions: In a pan, use 3/4 cup reserved pineapple juice, orange juice, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: gazpacho soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender and blend at high. Place in large sieve inside mixing bowl.
Press and stir with a spoon to extract as much liquid as possible.
Discard solids in sieve.
Taste and add more salt and vinegar if desired.
Chill before serving.
Makes 6 servings.
Serve fresh the day made.

title: holiday turketti
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: crock-pot ham
directions: Let cook overnight on low heat.

title: orzo with black beans and veggies
directions: Cook Orzo according to package directions.
Microwave broccoli (covered) on High 3 minutes.
Stir, microwave 2 minutes.
Add black beans, tomatoes, seasoning and Feta cheese.
Stir, microwave 1 minute on High. stir in Orzo, microwave 2 minutes on High.
Grate cheese to taste on each portion.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Blend well.
Add zucchini.
Sift flour together with baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to batter.
Put in pineapple and nuts.
Mix well. Bake until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake for about 1 hour.
Cool on wire rack before removing from pan.
Wrap and store overnight to develop before serving.

title: marinated tomatoes and onions
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients for marinade together.
Layer onion, tomatoes and parsley in bowl.
Add dressing and marinate overnight.

title: ice water pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions, red peppers and garlic in a large bowl. Cover with ice cubes and let stand 3 hours.
Drain vegetables and remove garlic, if desired.
Make syrup by combining vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Pour equal amounts of syrup into 2 large pots and bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables and bring to a rolling boil.
Pack into hot sterilized jars.
Fill to brim and seal.

title: layered jello salad
directions: This turns out very pretty.
I use a cake Bundt pan with Teflon coating or a large Tupperware mold.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Fill pie shell with sliced peaches.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 375° until custard is set.

title: kraft caramel brownies
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk and cake mix.
Spread 1/2 of cake mix into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 8 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with evaporated milk (microwave okay, stir frequently).
Remove cake from oven.
Pour and spread caramel mixture over cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top of caramel mixture (go easy on the chips or it will be too sweet). Top with remaining cake mixture.
Bake 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: easy chicken cacciatore
directions: Brown chicken in olive oil with garlic.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Add mushrooms while browning.
Add tomatoes. Cover and cook until chicken is tender.
Serve over spaghetti or rice.

title: ricotta cheese cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Add chocolate chips on top.
Mix eggs, cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes.
When cool, put sifted confectioners sugar on top.

title: dump cake
directions: Put ingredients as listed in pan.
Bake in oven at 375 degrees for 1 hour.

title: mt. gretna chocolate fondue
directions: Combine chocolate and cream in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chocolate is melted and smooth.
Add sugar and peanut butter; continue cooking until slightly thickened.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Pour into fondue pot.
Serve warm with fondue dippers.
Makes about 2 cups fondue.

title: rhubarb orange pie
directions: Line pie plate.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, butter and juice to egg yolks; beat thoroughly.
Add remaining sugar, flour and salt; beat well.
Add rhubarb to yolk mixture and stir well.
Gently fold in meringue.
Pour into pastry shell; sprinkle top with pecans.
Bake on bottom rack at 375° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 45 minutes more.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding, sugar and milk in a small bowl.
Beat slowly with mixer (about 1 minute).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on cake. Makes enough for two 9-inch layers.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: one casserole dinner(from 1975 edition)
directions: Saute hamburger until brown.
Meanwhile, boil macaroni until tender.
Drain macaroni and combine with meat; add tomato sauces and seasonings.
Fold in corn.
Place mixture in a 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into walnut size balls. Bake on cookie sheet.
Do not let balls touch each other.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour batter into a large rectangle dish (9 x 13). Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done. Cool completely.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, shortening and spices in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cool and add vinegar, then eggs one at a time. Beat after each addition.
Mix soda in the water.
Combine flour, soda and water with sugar mixture.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with 3-inch cookie cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken-rice-artichoke salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions; cool.
Mix in all remaining ingredients.
Mix mayonnaise and artichoke juice; stir well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut shortening in until size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon of water over mixture. Gently toss with fork.
Repeat until all is moistened. Form ball. Roll out on floured board and shape into pie pan.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix well in order given and pour into greased casserole. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: finger paints
directions: Mix together sugar, cornstarch and water until smooth and thick.
(An adult should be there or to do it.)
Remove from heat; cool.
Spoon mixture into muffin tin or small bowls.
Add food coloring and a pinch of soap flakes or a drop of detergent into each portion.
Stir.
Have fun; all ages.

title: pink cloud
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put into a 13 x 9-inch pan lined with graham cracker crumbs.
Cover with foil.
May be served either frozen or refrigerated.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Slice mushrooms, pepper and cheese.
Cut up onions.
Combine together.
Mix oil, vinegar and seasoning.
Pour over mushroom combination; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: silk cocoa cream low-fat dessert
directions: In a small bowl sprinkle gelatin over water; allow to stand 2 minutes to soften.
In medium saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa; stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is very hot.
Add gelatin mixture, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into medium bowl.
Refrigerate until mixture is chilled (do not allow to gel).

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain and chop the artichoke hearts.
Mix with the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 25 minutes at 325°.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Mix brown sugar and flour.
Add cream and butter.
Heat and let cool a little.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In a large bowl, beat together the applesauce, egg, oil and honey.
Set the bowl aside.

title: walnut chicken
directions: In small bowl, blend soy sauce into cornstarch.
Stir in sherry, gingerroot, sugar, salt and red pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in skillet for 2 minutes over medium-high heat.
Stir-fry green pepper and onion for 2 minutes.
Remove to bowl.
Stir-fry walnuts 1 to 2 minutes until golden.
Remove to bowl.
Add remaining oil, if necessary, and reheat.
Stir-fry chicken for 2 to 3 minutes, until all pieces are white.
Stir soy sauce mixture and then stir into chicken.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Stir in vegetables and walnuts.
Cook 1 minute until heated through. Serve over hot rice.
Serves 2.

title: pavlova
directions: Beat egg whites with an electric beater until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar beating constantly.
Keep beating for approximately 10 minutes.
Fold in cornflour and lemon juice. Drop in "blob" on baking paper on a cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: apple custard dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine dry cake mix and coconut in large bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Put apple pieces into pan.
Sprinkle crumbly mixture over apples.
Combine water and lemon juice in glass measure.
Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until top is lightly browned.
Set to cool before serving.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter 7 x 5 x 3-inch casserole dish. Melt margarine; add flour to make a thick paste.
Add liquid from both cans of asparagus; add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Stir in grated cheese.
Add asparagus and stir until asparagus comes to pieces.
Add chopped boiled eggs. Pour into casserole dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Bake until crumbs are brown or about 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix as much of the ingredients for the amount of salad you need.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: german corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick, easy and good cake
directions: Mix cake with pineapple. Use cake mix instructions and bake according to directions. Do not add water. Do not drain pineapple.

title: presidential salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in strawberries, blueberries and pineapple.
Pour half of gelatin mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until almost set.
Combine sour cream and cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Spread over chilled layer. Gradually spoon remaining gelatin mixture over sour cream layer; chill until firm.

title: steamed cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into wedges.
Sprinkle with salad dressing.
Place on stove; cook until tender.
Sprinkle pepper on top.

title: cheese sticks(microwave)
directions: In a medium microwave-safe bowl, place cream cheese and butter. Heat on High 1 1/2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Into cream cheese mixture, stir Parmesan, mustard and hot pepper sauce; mix well. With knife, spread an equal amount of cheese mixture onto half of each breadstick.
Place the poppy seed, chives, sesame seed and paprika on separate pieces of waxed paper.
Lightly roll 4 breadsticks in each of the coatings.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and sour cream.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine rest of ingredients and sprinkle over batter.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 15 servings.

title: freezer zucchini jam
directions: Cook first two ingredients for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the next three ingredients and boil for 8 minutes.
Set off the stove and stir in the jello.
Let set until cool.
Pour into small containers and freeze.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix all together; chill several hours in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on high 8 to 10 hours.
During last half of cooking time, remove lid and cook uncovered.
Stir occasionally.

title: shortbread(scotland)
directions: After measuring sifted flour, sift sugar.
Mix with flour and sift twice.
Blend flour and sugar mixture with softened butter with hands until butter is absorbed (about 20 minutes).
Roll out about 3/8 to 1/2-inch thick and cut in desired shapes.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 20 to 25 minutes, just until edges are light brown (325°).

title: stromboli bread
directions: Roll pizza dough; grease large pan.
Place pizza dough on pan. In a bowl put vegetables, ham, pepperoni, Mozzarella and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Spread on pizza dough; leave 1/2 inch at end. Roll; tuck ends.
Bake at 375° for half hour or a little longer until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: hot christmas punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until hot.
Simmer for 30 minutes before serving.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Pare and cut eggplant into 1/4-inch thick slices, dip each in flour and then into beaten eggs with salt and pepper.
Saute slices in hot oil until golden brown on both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
Arrange a layer of eggplant on the bottom of a 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with a layer of tomato sauce.
Combine parsley and Parmesan.
Sprinkle on top.
Add Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers until eggplant is used and cover with spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese is lightly brown and filling is bubbling hot.

title: lemon bar deluxe
directions: Sift together flour and confectioners sugar; cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press into 13x9x2-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° 20-25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into churn.
Start freezer.
Add ice and ice cream salt until full.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet, cook noodles according to package directions.
Add seasoning packets; drain off most of liquid. Stir in mushroom soup and milk.
Add chicken and broccoli.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: barbecue sauce by r. d. brooks
directions: Mix and simmer for 30 minutes.
This recipe makes 3 gallons of sauce.
I usually pour the sauce back into the vinegar jars while it is hot and the jars will seal.
I keep the rest in the refrigerator.

title: western pralines(an old favorite from the early 1900's)
directions: In a large (3 1/2-quart) heavy saucepan combine sugar, soda, buttermilk and salt.
Cook over high heat about 5 minutes.
Stir often and scrape bottom of pan.
Mixture will foam up.
Add butter and pecans over medium heat; continue cooking, stirring constantly, and scraping bottom of pan until candy reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and cool slightly, about 2 minutes. Beat with a spoon until thick and creamy.
Drop from a tablespoon onto sheet of aluminum foil or waxed paper.
Let cool.
Makes about 20 pralines, 2 inches in diameter.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: milk way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars in a small amount of milk in saucepan or microwave.
Stirring constantly; cool.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl, mixing well.
Stir in melted candy bars.
Pour into ice cream freezer container and freeze.

title: light garden spaghetti
directions: In large saucepan cook and stir onion and garlic in margarine. Stir in flour, bouillon and thyme.
Gradually add milk.
Over medium heat cook and stir until thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Add broccoli, carrots and mushrooms; heat through.
Serve over hot cooked spaghetti.
Calories per serving: 260; fat 7 g.

title: mandarin oranges in a cloud
directions: In double boiler top mix gelatin, 1/4 cup sugar and salt. Stir in egg yolks, then slowly stir in milk. Cook over boiling water, stirring constantly, until mixture coats back of spoon. Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon peel.

title: mocha egg nog
directions: Blend egg nog, milk, coffee and extract; chill.
Whisk in whipped cream.
Sprinkle with chocolate.

title: brownie peanut butter bites
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine brownie mix, water, oil and egg. Fill paper-lined mini muffin cups about 1/2 full. Press 1 peanut butter cup into batter in each cup. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 40 to 48 pieces.

title: christmas penuche(original recipe)
directions: You will also need 1 candy thermometer.

title: many way meatballs
directions: Mix beef, crumbs, onion, egg and salt.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, water and parsley.
Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes. Stir now and then while cooking.
Serves 4 or 5.
(Can use cream of vegetable soup, Cheddar cheese soup, cream of mushroom soup or cream of celery soup in place of tomato soup.)

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken in boiling salted water.
Add onion, if you like. Put chicken pieces in bottom of a casserole dish.
Put thawed broccoli spears over the chicken.
After mixing both cans of soup with the water, pour over the chicken and broccoli.
Top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Simmer chicken with small amount of salt until tender.
(I use pressure cooker.)
Bone and cut into small pieces.
Place in rectangular casserole dish.
Add mushrooms.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rave review coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into 3 greased 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: reese's peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the oleo, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Combine and add the flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt. Stir in the peanut butter chips.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve jello and sugar in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and beat well.
Add pineapple, nuts, vanilla and 7-Up and blend. Chill until firm.

title: never fail black cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and 1/2 cup of milk. Sift together dry ingredients.
