Alternate dry ingredients with water.
Stir well after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Fry in a large skillet.
Add pork chops and brown very slowly on both sides; lift out.
Pour off excess fat.
Spread rice over bottom of skillet.
Add water and sprinkle with one teaspoon salt.
Arrange pork chops over rice. Sprinkle with remaining salt.
Add onion and tomatoes.
Spoon on corn.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat. Cover and simmer 25 or 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add water, if needed.
Serves 6.

title: baked chicken breast
directions: Mix preserves and dressing.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken, then dressing mixture.
Cover with foil.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together the 2 cups flour, butter and powdered sugar.
Pat in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes or until light brown.
While the first layer is baking, beat eggs and add the remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust and bake 15 to 25 minutes until the top layer is set and custard-like. When cool, cut into small squares.

title: master mix pancakes or waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Cook on hot lightly oiled griddle or waffle iron.
Makes 12 pancakes or 6 waffles.

title: toffee
directions: Butter square pan 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Spread nuts in pan.
Heat sugar and butter to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil for 7 minutes, stirring constantly over medium heat.
Immediately spread mix evenly over nuts in pan.
Sprinkle with chips, cover with foil until chips melt.
Spread over candy.
While hot, cut into squares.
Chill until firm.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° until thick or approximately 1 hour for onion and rice to be done.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Melt bacon grease in skillet.
Add onion, green pepper, and rice.
Cook and stir over
high heat until lightly
browned.
Then add tomato sauce and
seasonings.
Mix well.
Bring to boil, and add meat which has been browned.
Cover tightly, and turn heat very low.
Simmer until rice is done.
Add water
if
necessary.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 1 unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: pecan fruit salad
directions: Toss with 1/2 pint sour cream and refrigerate.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Mix well.
Place in ovenproof serving bowl.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 325° until hot.
Serve immediately with Triscuits crackers.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil until vegetables are tender. Cut cheese in 10 (1-ounce) slices and add to vegetable mixture until cheese is melted.

title: more beans, please
directions: Brown beef and onion and drain. Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: onion potatoes
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Place soup mix, oil and potatoes in large bag and shake to coat.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat with rotary mixer all ingredients until smooth.
Fry on hot griddle.

title: sharp cheese and onion spread
directions: Grate cheese.
When cheese is at room temperature, combine with other ingredients.
Mix until smooth enough to spread on crackers.
Garnish with tiny crisp bits of bacon.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Place steak in a glass dish.
Combine ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Remove meat, discard marinade.
Grill over hot coals until meat reaches desired doneness.
Slice into thin strips across the grain to serve.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a pot. Stir occasionally. Boil on medium heat. Simmer 1 hour or more to thicken. Follow general rules for canning. Makes 6 to 9 pints.

title: old fashion white bread
directions: Heat milk to 120°.
In large mixing bowl, combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar and warmed milk.
Mix with dough mixer or by hand for 5 minutes.
Add 2 3/4 cups flour and continue kneading 3 more minutes.
If sticky, knead enough of remaining 1/2 cup flour to form stiff dough.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once, to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Cook vegetables for about 20 minutes and then drain.
Mix all ingredients together, except crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Then put crumbs on top, drizzle with 1/2 stick melted butter
and bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and egg; mixing until well blended.
Set aside.
Add combined oil and eggs; mixing just until moistened.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Reserve 2 cups batter; pour remaining batter into greased and floured 9-inch Bundt pan. Pour cream cheese mixture over batter.
Carefully spoon reserved batter over cream cheese mixture, spreading to cover.

title: apple cake
directions: Peel and slice apples in bowl.
Stir into the apples the cinnamon and 2 1/2 tablespoons sugar.
Set this aside.
Grease and flour dome pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except apples) and put half of batter into dome pan.
Sprinkle half of the apple mixture and then add rest of batter.
Top with remaining apples and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Enjoy!

title: toasted pecans
directions: Mix pecans with butter.
Spread pecans on a baking sheet. Sprinkle with salt.

title: broccoli trees
directions: Prepare a dip by combining the sour cream, mayonnaise, sugar lemon juice, and basil in a medium size mixing bowl. To make the trees, cut each carrot in half widthwise and then lengthwise into four pieces. Assemble on a plate by laying three carrot pieces side by side for a trunk with the broccoli florets as the leaves. Spread dip under the trunks for the forest floor.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Roll hamburger into balls. Brown and drain off grease. Add cream of mushroom soup and water. Cook on low until hamburger is done. Goes great served with mashed potatoes.

title: apple pie
directions: Fill pie shell with apples.
Mix sugar, nutmeg, salt, cinnamon and lemon juice, sprinkle over apples and dot with butter.
Moisten edge of crust with cold water.
Bake 425° for 40 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Combine mustard, horseradish, cream cheese and parsley flakes. Spread each dough slice into a rectangle.
Spread mixture on each rectangle and a ham slice on each.
Roll jelly roll fashion and cut into pieces.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar is dissolved and mixture comes to a full boil.
Add butter; continue cooking, stirring occasionally until candy thermometer reaches 280°.
Stir in peanuts; continue cooking, stirring constantly, until candy thermometer reaches 305°.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda.
Pour mixture onto two buttered cookie sheets; spread about 1/4-inch thick.
Cool completely; bread into pieces.
Yield: 2 pounds.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine well and serve with veggies or bread chunks in scooped out pumpernickel bread.

title: tuna buns
directions: Mix all ingredients, except buns.
Divide mixture evenly and spread on buns.
Close buns and wrap each in square of foil.
Heat 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 hot sandwiches.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with 6 ounces chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs and mashed bananas.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes 2 small loaves or 1 large loaf.

title: rice dressing casserole(quick and easy!  throw in dish and bake.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish that is covered tightly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: congo bars
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, vanilla and Crisco.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Add pecans. Pour in pan.
Spread with hands.
Bake 30 minutes in 350°
oven. Cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Whip pudding with 3 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer graham crackers in pan (use whole graham crackers, do not crumble).
Alternate layers with pudding and ending with crackers.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, shaking off excess.
In a large nonstick pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add beef, saute until browned, about 6 minutes.
Place on a plate.

title: corn custard
directions: Mix and cook the first 7 ingredients until thick.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with the crushed crackers and 1/2 stick margarine.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: kielbasa pasta salad
directions: In skillet, simmer sausage, covered in the 1/2 cup water for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Drain and slice kielbasa; set aside.
In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
Cook mushrooms in reserved drippings for 2 minutes.
Stir in sugar, flour, salt and pepper; add the 3/4 cup water and the vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add kielbasa, macaroni, bacon and parsley.
Toss together lightly.
Garnish with additional snipped parsley if desired.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Saute 3/4 cup chopped onion with 2 tablespoons oleo.
Add the paprika, pepper, sugar, table mustard, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and vinegar.
Blend all ingredients thoroughly and cook for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add the chipped ham and continue cooking until ham is thoroughly heated.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, tear into bites and place on bottom of buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Spread Veg-All on top of chicken.
Mix soup and broth; spread over Veg-All.
Add topping.

title: applesauce meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and roll in small balls.
Cover with one
can tomato sauce.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Grease pan.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar in large bowl.
Put in shortening. Add dissolved yeast and buttermilk; mix well.
Knead.
Roll out on floured surface.
Cut out.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.
Dough may be refrigerated until needed.

title: glazed ham
directions: Boil smoked shoulder on stove in water for about 3 hours.
Then place in roaster and stick whole cloves into top of ham.
Cover with brown sugar and add 1 cup water.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 2 hours at 400°.

title: rainbow crayons
directions: In an old pan over low heat, melt 2 to 4 crayons of the same color.
When melted, pour into your container.
Clean pan while still warm by wiping with paper towel.
After the first layer hardens just to a firm stage, melt more crayons and add a different colored layer.
Repeat until you fill container.
Let harden and tap container.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add applesauce, flour and all the fruits and nuts, dredged in flour.	Mix well and put in tube pans, then put whole cherries on top.
Cook in slow oven.
This makes 2 fruitcakes.

title: mini pecan pies
directions: Blend the first 2 ingredients.
Stir in the flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape dough into 24 (1-inch) balls.
Press into ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin pans.
Put dough over bottom and up sides.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place potatoes into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix next 6 ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed cornflakes; then top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and beaten eggs.
Add flavoring mixed with buttermilk; mix well.
Pour mixture into pie shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: meatballs with mushroom sauce
directions: Cook the bacon in a large skillet until brown and crisp. Remove and drain on paper towels, reserving the fat from the bacon. Put the ground beef in a large mixing bowl.
Cook the chopped onions in the butter until they are soft but not brown.
Remove the onions and add them to the beef.
Lightly brown the bread crumbs and crushed garlic in the pan used for the onions, adding a little more butter if needed.
Put the bread in with the beef and onions. Add the eggs, salt, pepper and oregano.
Mix the ingredients well until they are thoroughly blended.

title: cheddar cheese muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups or use foil or paper baking cups.
Thoroughly mix flour, baking powder, salt and pepper in a large bowl.
Add cheese.
Toss flour and cheese with fingers to distribute cheese evenly.
Whisk egg and mustard in small bowl. When well mixed, whisk in milk and butter.
Pour over flour mixture.
Fold in gently with a rubber spatula, just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Scoop batter into muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until springy to the touch in the center. Cool on rack.
Makes 12 regular or 36 miniature muffins.

title: carrot-basil bake
directions: Peel and shred carrots.
Melt butter; add water, salt and parsley flakes and basil.
Stir into carrots.
Microwave on High power for 15 to 17 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking time.

title: raisin sauce
directions: Boil vinegar, water and raisins together.
Add mixture made of sugar, flour and mustard mixed with a small amount of water.
Boil again long enough to thicken.
Very good.

title: meat loaf
directions: In blender put pepper, egg, onion, milk and 1/2 cup ketchup, blend well.
Pour over ground beef and mix.
Add bread crumbs and mix.
Line a loaf pan with foil and pack mixture in it.
Cover with remaining ketchup.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat loaf pulls away from pan (about 1/2 inch).

title: apple relish
directions: Combine apples, onion and pickles and set aside.
In a separate bowl, combine sugar and vinegar.
Stir well.
Pour vinegar mixture over apple mixture and toss gently to coat.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.

title: deep dish chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in large saucepan.
Gradually stir in evaporated milk and water.
Add chocolate; cook and stir over medium heat until chocolate is melted and mixture boils. Stir in vanilla.
Pour into baked crust.
Chill for 3 hours before serving.
Serve with meringue or whipped topping.

title: sausage roll-ups
directions: Wrap Smokies with bacon and toothpick.
Sprinkle with packed brown sugar until thoroughly covered (usually 1/2 pound sugar). Cover with foil.
Let refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes covered with foil.
Uncover and bake additional 15 minutes or until bacon is crispy.
Best if in glass dish.

title: roast beef tenderloin
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spread 2 tablespoons of butter over beef.
Sprinkle liberally with pepper.
Wrap in 1/4 pound bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Place on rack in roasting pan just large enough to accommodate beef.
Bake until thermometer inserted in thickest part of meat registers 120° for rare, about 30 minutes. Transfer beef to heated platter and tent with foil to keep warm.

title: hard times cake
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; set 1 cup aside for topping.
Dissolve soda in milk; add it to eggs and to dry mixture.
Stir thoroughly.
Add raisins.
Pour into greased loaf pan; sprinkle on topping.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beer rolls
directions: Preheat oven 400°.
Grease large muffin tin pan.
Stir Bisquick and sugar together; add beer.
Stir well.
Batter will be sightly sticky consistency.
Spoon into prepared muffin tins. Bake 400° for 12 - 14 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes 12 - 16 rolls.

title: camping stew
directions: Use enough ground beef for everyone in camp.
Fry meat over coals in large pot.
Have each person in camp bring a can of soup and let them pour it in the pot.
Do not use cream soups.
Heat and eat!

title: oatmeal cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop on cookie sheets, using a spoon slightly larger than a teaspoon.
Bake at 350° about 14 to 15 minutes. Take out of oven before looking done.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Cut 1 lemon into 1/8-inch thick slices and place in large pitcher.
Add sugar and press and stir together until sugar is dampened with lemon juice.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Juice remaining 3 lemons, add lemon juice, the water, tray of ice cubes, nutmeg and mint to pitcher.
Stir well.

title: microwave breakfast burritos
directions: Make scrambled eggs as usual.
Set aside.
Cook bacon or ham, drain, cool and chop up.
Mix ham or bacon with scrambled eggs.
On soft tortilla, spread ketchup.
Place on slice of cheese and add scoop of egg mixture.
Roll and pop in microwave 15 to 30 seconds. These may be prepared early and frozen until ready to eat.
Wrap tightly in Saran Wrap to freeze.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan and add onion and celery.
Saute and remove from heat.
Add other ingredients.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place 2 boxes of frozen chopped broccoli (thawed), pour ingredients over broccoli and mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until mixture bubbles.

title: apple cream pie
directions: Put apples in saucepan with sugar and water.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 10 to 20 minutes or until apples are tender. Drain, reserving syrup, cool apples slightly and put in 9-inch pie pan lined with pastry.
Beat eggs and cream together and stir in reserved syrup.
Pour over apples.
Bake in pre-heated moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: mountain sayings
directions: *BLKLIN more) walking around as if shopping, etc., representing the following topics:
LIGHTS, GIFTS, CARDS, CROWDS, MUSIC, VACATION, PARTIES, FAMILY, FOOD and MONEY.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Put meat, flour, salt and pepper in a paper bag and shake to coat the meat.
Meanwhile, saute sliced onion in 2 tablespoons oil until golden.
Add mushrooms and cook until tender.
Add the meat, stirring constantly to brown the floured meat.
Add the bouillon and cook over low heat until thickened.
Add wine and continue to simmer several minutes.
Before serving, stir in sour cream; mix thoroughly.
Be sure to heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach, discarding stems.
Pat dry on paper towels. Tear and put in bowl.
Add onion and sprinkle with pepper.
Chill. At serving time slowly fry bacon in a skillet until crisp.
Add vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and salt to skillet.
Gradually add spinach, tossing just until leaves are coated and wilted slightly. Place salad in 4 bowls.
Garnish with chopped egg.

title: easy shepherd's pie
directions: Using leftover steak bites, add drained peas and carrots. Place mashed potatoes in large casserole dish, making a bowl in the center of the potatoes.
Put steak bites into this "bowl" and place in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: homestead salad
directions: Mix green beans and mixed vegetables together; cook and cool. Rinse and drain kidney beans.
Mix sugar, flour, prepared mustard and vinegar together.
Cook until thick; cool.
Stir vegetables into cooled thickened mixture.
Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: quick hamburger dish
directions: Cook beef well and drain all grease off.
Add all ingredients and cook on top of stove for 20 minutes or bake in a pie shell at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Also can be cooked as a casserole.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the peanut butter, milk powder and honey.
Stir in peanuts and raisins.
Sprinkle with water.
Mix until well combined.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in saucepan.
Cook on medium heat.
Bring to boil.
Take off burner.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and pecans (if desired).
Spoon out on wax paper to cool.
Yields approximately 20 cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Add butter.
Fold in next 4 ingredients.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Add crumbs.
Bake at 300° to 350° until bubbly and top is brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Boil first 7 ingredients in double boiler until thick.
Stir continuously.
When thick, add marshmallows.
Mix well and cool. Add pineapple, well drained.
Whip the whipping cream and fold with other ingredients.
Pour in 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put in refrigerator. Works well made night before.

title: caramels
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly, until candy reaches soft ball stage or 245° on a candy thermometer.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased jelly roll pan. Let cool, then cut and wrap in waxed paper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, then add flour.
Shape dough in rounded balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press cookie dough with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: christmas pickles
directions: Cook all of this until it is tender.
Put into sterilized jars while hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute chopped onion and chopped pepper in oleo.
Mix in corn, rice, pimento, sugar and egg.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle grated cheese and paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: working mom stroganoff
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown mushrooms and cook onion in butter until tender.
Add soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until bubbly.
Add sour cream just before serving. Serve over cooked noodles.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry and drain sausage and bacon; mix together.
Butter long casserole dish and line bottom with half of the bread.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese; add all the sausage and bacon.
Layer bread and cheese again.
Beat eggs; add milk, Worcestershire, pepper, salt and mustard.
Pour over meat mixture and cover. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325°, uncovered, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve on salad.

title: sheet cake
directions: Melt and blend all ingredients.
Pour this mixture over hot cake.

title: red clam sauce
directions: Brown onion in oil, then add tomatoes.
Cook for 10 minutes. Add clams, juice, seasonings.
Press in garlic.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over linguine.

title: kielbasa skillet
directions: Slice sausage.
Place vegetable oil in a large skillet and saute the sausage, onion and garlic until onion is wilted but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients, cover and cook until vegetables are tender and most of liquid has been absorbed, about 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bread in orange shells
directions: Cornbread and gingerbread can be mixed according to directions and cooked in hollowed out orange shells.
Gives a wonderful flavor to the bread.
Cook in coals for 30 minutes.
Can also be baked in a Dutch oven at about 400° with coals on top and bottom.

title: old fashioned chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco, then add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients by sifting together.
Then add dry ingredients and milk alternately to creamed ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, vanilla, 1/2 cup butter, chocolate syrup, beaten
eggs and flour.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rice, broccoli, cheese casserole
directions: Cook rice first; set aside.
Chop celery and onions fine. Saute both in small frying pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
In 2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients and mix together.
Cook with cover on for 30 minutes, stirring once in the middle.

title: corn flake muffins(serves 12)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix flakes and milk.
Let stand 2 minutes until cereal is soft.
Add egg and oil.
Beat well.
Add flour mix.
Stir only until combined.
Fill 12 greased muffin pan cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chicken and rice dressing
directions: Warm 1 cup of butter in microwave until it is melted.
In large mixing bowl, add bell pepper, onion, rice and all soups.
Stir well.
Pour half of butter into large casserole dish then add rice mixture.
Place chicken on top of the rice mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour the rest of the butter on top of the chicken.
Place in pre-heated oven at 275 degrees F for 2-1/2 hours.

title: cheesecake
directions: Cream cheese, add eggs, mandarin peel and extract.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: salad
directions: Place salad greens in a bowl.
Press garlic to taste. Sprinkle salt until you think you have enough and then add more. Pour olive oil in a circle and an X.
Add 8 shakes of the vinegar (assumes you have a shakable lid).
Mix well and serve immediately.

title: crab meat newburg appetizer
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add flour and salt.
Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened and smooth.
Add cheese, stirring until blended.
Blend in remaining ingredients, except parsley. Put into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 15 minutes, or until heated through.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with Melba toast or toast points.
Makes 25 servings.

title: apple roll
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in Crisco.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll dough out to about 1/4-inch thick.
Keep in oblong shape.
Spread with soft butter, then a generous amount of chopped apples and sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and roll tightly.
Cut into slices about 2-inch thick and place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Keep slices close together.
On top of each roll, place a slice of apple.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes. Jonathan apples do well!

title: chinese crunch salad
directions: Slice cabbage very thin.
Toss with chopped onion.
Melt butter.
Crumble Ramen noodles in package.
Brown noodles, almonds and sesame seed.
Cool mixture.
Mix oil, vinegar, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Toss all ingredients together.
Can be made ahead, but store in separate containers until ready to serve.

title: southern vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large cooking kettle.
Boil for 1 hour stirring often.
One-half cup of NutraSweet can be substituted if you can't have sugar.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine the ingredients with a head of shredded cabbage and 1 grated carrot.
Chill.

title: puffy french toast
directions: Combine milk, egg and Bisquick.
Heat shortening.
Dip bread into mixture.
Cook until lightly brown.
Top with butter and syrup.

title: curried fruit bake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Drain fruit and arrange in 13 x 9-inch oblong pan.
Pour mixture of remaining ingredients over fruit. Bake 15 minutes.
Baste with juice in pan; bake 15 minutes more.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients, except catsup.
Pat into 9 x 5-inch casserole dish.
Spread catsup over top.
Roast for 20 to 25 minutes or until well done in center (145°).
Pour off liquid and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate death pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with milk. Mix cocoa with sugar and add to cheese mixture. Stir in the vanilla and Cool Whip. Pour into crust. Serve topped with Cool Whip. This is ready to eat as soon as you get it made!

title: corn meal cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift the next 4 ingredients together.
Add to first mixture.
Form or divide into 2 rolls and refrigerate a few hours.
Overnight is better.
Slice thin and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Mix and cook Rice-A-Roni as directed, except without butter. Cool.
Mix curry, mayo and 1/2 artichoke heart liquid.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: crab bread(appetizer)
directions: Slice off the top of the bread round and hollow out the inside, saving the bread and the top.
Mix together all remaining ingredients and place mixture in the hollowed out bread round. Cover with reserved top.
Wrap in heavy foil and place on a baking sheet.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Before serving, cut up the reserved bread into cubes.
Place bread bowl on a serving plate and surround with bread cubes.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: pecan upside-down cake
directions: Combine butter,
brown
sugar
and 1 tablespoon boiling water in a
9-inch round cake pan; stir well.
Sprinkle pecans evenly over top;
set
aside.
Beat
egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; add
sugar
and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to yolk mixture alternately with remaining 3/4
cup
boiling
water,
beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Beat
well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until soft
peaks
form; gently fold into batter.
Pour batter evenly over pecans in pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto serving plate.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in milk.
Add 1/4 cup of butter, 3 tablespoons of sugar and salt.
Beat in almost 2 cups of flour gradually, keeping mixture satiny.
Add flour as needed. Cover dough; let rise 30 minutes or until doubled.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Cool until consistency of syrup and fold in drained fruit.
Turn into 7 x 11-inch dish.
Chill.
Top with dressing made by combining sugar and flour.
Blend all remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Cool and spread over salad.
Serves 6.

title: bacon horseradish dip
directions: Stir all ingredients until well mixed.
Cover and chill. Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate pecan coconut balls
directions: Mix together margarine, powdered sugar, Eagle Brand milk, coconut and pecans.
Roll into small balls and refrigerate.
Melt together paraffin wax and chocolate chips.
Dip balls in chocolate mixture with toothpicks and drop on wax paper.

title: shoe peg corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: green bean bake
directions: Reserve 1/2 cup green bean juice.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Bring milk to boil. Let cool.
Beat egg and add to milk.
Then add margarine and yeast mixture to milk along with the sugar and salt.
Mix in approximately 5 cups flour or until of good dough consistency. Grease hands and knead well.
Grease a large bowl and let dough set until double in bulk (about 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Roll out on floured board and cut out or pinch off rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° until lightly browned.

title: crispix mix
directions: Combine pretzels, cereal and nuts in a large microwave bowl. Stir remaining ingredients together and pour over the cereal mixture.
Gently mix to coat the cereal mixture.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.
Eat or store in an airtight container.

title: hawaiian spareribs
directions: Bake ribs 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Mix all other ingredients and cook together on low heat for about 45 minutes.
Pour fat off ribs; pour sauce over ribs.
Return to oven and bake for 50 minutes.

title: savory steak slices
directions: Trim excess fat.
Wipe steak with damp paper towels.
Mix soy sauce and rum in shallow dish big enough to hold steak.
Add steak.
Refrigerate, turning occasionally, for 24 hours.
Remove steak.
Brush lightly with oil.
Place in broiler pan without rack.
Broil 6 inches from heat 1 minute on each side.
Turn and broil 5 minutes longer.
Turn again; broil 5 minutes more until medium-rare.
Slice steak thinly on the diagonal.
Arrange slices and pour juices over meat.
Garnish with watercress and radishes (or anything else your heart desires).

title: date-nut bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 8 x 8-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cut in strips and roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Soak
peaches
in
cold
water overnight.
Cook in same water for
flavor.
Cook
until	tender.
Mash
peaches	and sweeten to own taste.
Add cinnamon, vanilla and remainder of sugar,
if needed.
Cut pastry dough in circles about 6-inches in diameter. Place the amount of peaches you want in each pie on the pastry. Fold
over	and
press
edges
together with a fork.
Fry in shortening until brown on both sides.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients until thick and clear.
Add strawberry Jell-O and red food coloring.
Mix until dissolved. Put berries in pie shell.
Pour topping over berries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chess cake
directions: Melt butter.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, stir into melted butter (do not use mixer):
cake mix and egg.
Press mixture down evenly on bottom of pan.
Mix together in bowl (use mixer):
eggs, confectioners sugar, cream cheese and lemon juice.

title: quick tangy punch
directions: Mix the Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Just before serving, add the carbonated drink.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain excess grease.
Add with all ingredients.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yellow squash and corn casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, then drain.
Brown onion and green pepper in 2 tablespoons butter.
Combine onion, green pepper, squash and corn.
Add egg, melted butter, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until firm.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Sift together and stir in flour and salt.
Mix in nuts. Chill dough; roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until set, but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
Cool; roll in sugar again.
Makes about 4 dozen 1 1/2-inch cookies.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Make into balls and bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes.
Roll in powder sugar.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Put in pan in order given.
Do not stir until done.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut chicken in pieces and put into a large pot.
Cover well with water and salt to taste.
Cook for 2 1/2 hours or until meat is tender enough to fall off of the bones.

title: clam canapes
directions: Cream everything, except clams.
Blend in clams.
Spread on crackers (Ritz or your choice).
Decorate with olive slices or pimento strips.
Can spread on thin buttered pieces of bread (white, rye or pumpernickel).
Can cut bread into fancy shapes. Toast under broiler.
Watch carefully.
Makes about 50.

title: homemade mincemeat
directions: Bring to boil tomatoes, lemon and vinegar; add sugar and spices.
Cook low and just before done, add raisins.
Put into jars hot and seal.

title: wing ding punch
directions: In a medium saucepan, heat the sugar and half of the pineapple juice until dissolved very good.
Put this into a very large bowl, then pour rest of pineapple juice in.
In your blender, blend 3 sliced bananas, 1 1/2 cups water and all of the lemonade.
Pour into the large bowl with rest of other mixture.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening, sugar and salt.
Mix water, egg and vinegar with a fork and add to flour.
Chill for 15 minutes.
Dough can be stored in refrigerator for 3 days or frozen until ready to use.
Makes 2 double crusts for 9-inch shell.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients except chocolate chips.
Mix batter until smooth, if batter is too thick add more milk.
Grease skillet, preheat until water dances on skillet.
Pour batter onto skillet.
Drop approximately 6 chocolate chips into each pancake.
Turn pancake over when bubbles form.

title: stuffed hungarian peppers
directions: Saute sausage until brown.
Mix crab meat with sausage. De-seed peppers and stuff sausage.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef mulligan
directions: Cut and cook potatoes.
Drain.
Saute finely diced onion.
(Or you can use onion powder).
In large pan, put potatoes, onion, 1 can cream-style corn and roast beef.
Add 1 stick of butter, 1 1/2 cans of milk, water, salt and pepper to taste.
Do not let boil, but simmer for about 15 minutes.
Stir from bottom often.
Good with salad, pickles and crackers.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix all ingredients and simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
While sauce is cooking, prepare lasagne noodles.
Use enough for one 13 x 9-inch pan, plus 2-quart casserole (about 10 to 12 noodles).

title: hot sausage roll
directions: Mix pastry; roll thin and spread.
Roll like a jellyroll. Refrigerate.
Slice thin (about 1/4-inch) and bake in 350° oven until brown.
Serve hot.
If the roll is about 1-inch around, these are good served as a party food.

title: easy potato pancakes
directions: Beat egg in a medium bowl.
Stir in all remaining ingredients in order until almost smooth.
Heat a lightly greased skillet or griddle, using 1/4 cup batter for each pancake.
Fry until golden brown, about 4 minutes on each side.
Serve hot with applesauce or sausages.

title: ham balls
directions: Combine ground meat, eggs, milk and cracker crumbs.
Mix well. Shape into balls (large walnut size).
Place in pan.
In bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Blend well and pour over balls. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in small amount of boiling water about 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine celery, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix well and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Melt butter.
Add flour and cook 1 minute.
Add chicken stock and half and half. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Pour over celery mixture.
Mix Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs and sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well by hand or electric blender.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes about 1 3/4 cup which is equivalent to 1 can of condensed milk.

title: rice pie
directions: Prepare pie crust, adding the nutmeg to the dry ingredients. Cook the rice in broth until liquid is absorbed.
Saute onion to translucent (in olive oil).
Mix rice, onion (scrape oil out of pan with rubber spatula) and cheese until well blended.
Add your salt and pepper.
Mix a little more and place mixture in bottom pie shell.
Cover with other half of shell and bake 1 hour at 350°. Crust will be golden brown.
This can be served warm or cold.

title: banana icing
directions: Mash bananas and mix with lemon juice.
Add sugar, cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is slightly thickened and glossy.
Spread on cake layers while still warm.

title: tortilla de patatus a la espanola(spanish omelet)
directions: Wash and peel potatoes and then cut into small cubes.
Heat 2 cups oil in a frying pan and add potatoes.
Fry until brown and relatively soft, stirring every once in a while.
Once fried, place potatoes in a separate bowl.
In another bowl, beat eggs forcefully with a fork.
Add the salt and stir until mixed.
Add the potatoes to the eggs.
In a large frying pan, add three tablespoons of oil to cover bottom of pan and heat.
When heated, add the egg and potato mixture.
Move the frying pan in a small circular motion so the omelet does not stick to the pan.
When the omelet comes away from the bottom of the pan, slide the omelet onto a plate (as to make flipping the eggs easier); turn the omelet over and cook the other side.
Use a spatula to lift the sides of the eggs so they do not stick to the pan.
When the eggs come off the pan, flip once more and heat for a minute.
Serves four to six people.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add oil.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add coffee.
Pour into cake batter slowly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli with parmesan sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cut the broccoli into florets.
Place them in a saucepan with 2 cups of water.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and drain immediately.
Place broccoli in a buttered ovenproof dish.

title: double decker blueberry pie
directions: Brown 2 pie crust shells.
In first browned crust, add 1 pint of berries, 3 tablespoons of butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Cut second browned crust and arrange over first layer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover with uncooked pie crust. Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: white chocolate icing
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Add buttermilk and bring to rapid boil.
Remove from heat and add sugar and flavoring.

title: diabetic peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, peanut butter, rind and vanilla together. Add egg and blend well. Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with orange juice. Blend well. Add raisins. Roll into balls, place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet, flatten with fork. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Store in airtight container. Taste better 24 hours after baking.

title: ghost toast
directions: Separate each biscuit into three parts and stretch them into "Spooky" ghost shapes.
Paint each with melted butter and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Bake	about
5 minutes or until brown at 375°.

title: blueberry jello
directions: Drain juice from fruit; mix fruit to jello and chill until firm.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend sugar into egg whites until fluffy.
Melt butter and set aside to cool.
Add flour, salt, vanilla, water and butter to the sugar mixture.
Beat until smooth.
On well-greased cookie sheet, pour batter into 3-inch circles.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
Lay the fortune paper into the center of cookie.
Fold cookie into thirds and bend the center gently.
If cookie gets hard to bend, reheat in oven for a minute.
Yields 30 Fortune Cookies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: pecan graham crackers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt oleo, butter and sugar in saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Add cup of pecans to mixture.
Place graham crackers on cookie sheet; pour mixture over crackers.
Cook at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: giant skippy oat cookies
directions: In medium bowl combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and oats.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended. Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture; by hand, mix until well combined.
Shape into 2-inch balls.
Place 6 balls on ungreased cookie sheet; flatten each to 3-inch diameter.
Bake in 350° oven 15 to 17 minutes or until golden.
Remove from cookie sheet, cool on wire rack.
Store in tightly covered container. Makes about 24 cookies.

title: nut goodie bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips, chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter together in a double boiler.
Pour 1/3 of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Add a layer of miniature marshmallows. Sprinkle 6 ounces of peanuts on top.
Pour remaining chocolate mixture over the top.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut in squares. Makes 24 to 30 bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: holiday dip
directions: *May substitute 1 cup boiled shrimp.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: Boil water; stir in jello and yogurt.
Add raspberries.
Chill until set.
Good and low fat!!

title: pan-roasted lamb chops
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Season the lamb with salt and pepper. Heat a large ovenproof frying pan and add the oil.
Brown the chops quickly over medium-high heat.
Place the whole pan with the lamb in the oven.
Roast the lamb chops 2 minutes per side for medium rare.
After 4 minutes in the oven, remove the pan and set the frying pan in a warm place and allow the meat to rest in the pan another 2 minutes.
This will relax the meat and finish the cooking.
Serve with onions sauteed with yogurt and sesame oil.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pistachio pudding salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
For a lighter version, omit marshmallows and substitute "lite" Cool Whip or yogurt.
Use sugar-free pudding mix and pineapple in its own juice.
Mix the same.

title: oven fried fish fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Coat fillets with mayonnaise.
Dredge in breadcrumbs.
Arrange fillets on baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake 12 minutes or until fillets flake easily with fork.
Serves 4.

title: green salad with pine nuts
directions: Boil garlic in water for 5 minutes.
Remove garlic and crush in a wooden bowl.
Add Dijon mustard to make a paste.
Add vinegar and oil to taste and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over romaine lettuce, toss and add pine nuts.

title: egg pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk.
Sift together flour, salt and sugar. Mix together.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Good plain or with your favorite syrup.

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Spread refried beans on a 10-inch serving platter.
Spread sour cream on top of refried beans.
Arrange lettuce on sour cream.
Spread salsa over lettuce.
Arrange Cheddar cheese over salsa.
Sprinkle black olives over Cheddar cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Saute beef and sausage separately.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put a tablespoon of mixture on each slice of party rye.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes until bubbles or browns.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Makes 24 mini pizzas.

title: fish fillet dinner
directions: Alternate potatoes and broccoli around edge of 9-inch plate; sprinkle with water.
Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave on High (100%) until hot, 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
`Place fish fillet in center of plate.
Cover with vented plastic wrap and microwave until fish flakes easily with fork, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes; drain. Place margarine, lemon juice and tarragon in small dish.
Microwave uncovered on High (100%) until margarine is melted, 30 to 40 seconds; spoon over fish and vegetables.
Makes 1 serving meal.

title: chicken crescents
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put into rectangle.
Fold to center.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetarian baked beans
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: carrot fig bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine figs and water in a blender or food processor. Puree.
Set aside.

title: pastry pie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix together all of the ingredients. Stir with a fork until thoroughly mixed. Do not overwork the dough.
Shape this mixture into a ball and place it between two pieces of wax paper that has been dusted with flour.
Roll the pastry into a circle large enough to fit in a 9-inch pie pan. Spray pan with a nonfat cooking spray.

title: turkey bone gumbo
directions: After turkey has been carved, put bones in plenty of water. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours until meat falls off bones.
Make a roux of bacon drippings and flour.
Add onions, garlic, bell pepper and celery.
Cook until wilted.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: salmon balls
directions: Pour juice in a measuring cup and set aside.
Break egg in salmon.
Separate salmon with a fork; add flour.
Use 1/4 cup salmon juice and add baking powder and stir.
Let foam; add to mixture and drop by spoon into hot oil and fry until golden brown. Serves 4 to 5.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Slice carrots 1/4-inch thick and cook in enough water to cover.
Cook until done but do not overcook.
Drain and cool. Heat remaining ingredients, stirring, until sugar is dissolved. Cool completely.
Add carrots, mix well and refrigerate at least 24 hours.
This will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: green bean deluxe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook beans as directed on package; drain. In medium saucepan, melt 1/4 cup margarine.
Saute onion in margarine until crisp-tender.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream, cheese and beans.
Mix well; pour in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In small bowl, combine bread crumbs and melted oleo.
Sprinkle over beans.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: nancy reagan's vienna chocolate bars
directions: Cream butter with egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar. Add flour and knead with fingers.
Pat out on greased cookie sheet 3/8 inch thick.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until lightly browned. Remove from oven and spread with jelly and top with chocolate chips.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff.
Fold in remaining cup of sugar and nuts. Gently spread on top of jelly and chocolate.
Bake for about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: vanilla or chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour into ice cream freezer container and fill with whole milk to full mark.
Follow ice cream freezer instructions.

title: chess pie cake
directions: Mix well and spread in bottom of sheet pan (oblong).
Mix with fork.

title: cheese appetizers
directions: Mix first 5 items well; add flour, then Rice Krispies.
Spoon out in teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Dip caps in melted butter and place upside down in a shallow baking pan.
Finely chop 1/4 cup of the mushroom stems and saute well with green onion in remaining butter, adding more butter if necessary.
Add water.
Lightly stir in stuffing.
Spoon mixture into mushrooms caps.
Bake at 350° until hot, about 10 minutes.

title: cocoa krispie roll
directions: Cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter and 2 tablespoons butter.
Add cereal until well coated. Press into buttered jelly roll pan.
Melt 1/3 cup butter with milk over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Sift powdered sugar and cocoa into mixture.
Blend thoroughly.

title: fried squash
directions: Slice squash into 1/8-inch slices.
Batter in corn meal and salt and pepper to taste.
Heat corn oil in skillet until bubbling.
Fry slices in single layer until golden brown.

title: corn salad
directions: Saut corn and onion in oil until onion is slightly softened. Mix remaining veggies with warm corn and onion.
Dress salad with favorite vinaigrette dressing or bottled Italian dressing.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: sister gustie's corn pudding
directions: Mix well.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter in an iron skillet.
Pour mixture into the butter.
Bake at 400° to 450° until brown.

title: ham and cheese delights
directions: Unroll and seal the seam lines of the rolls.
Spread the rolls with spicy mustard.
Place ham and cheese on the rolls.
Roll up and seal the edges.
Cut with a sharp knife.
Bake at 375° for about 12 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: chicken fiesta
directions: Saute chicken in olive oil until done.
Sprinkle chicken with pepper while sauteing.
About half of the way through cooking chicken, add bell pepper and onion.
When onion and bell pepper seem to be getting limp, add tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 15 minutes, or until sauce warms up good.
Add the shredded cheese to the top of each chicken breast.
Make sure the pepper and onion are around and on top of each chicken breast, so the cheese can get on all of it at the same time.
After cheese is melted, serve.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Stir in water gradually.
Cook till bubbly and thickened, then cook for 1 minute longer.
Stir 1/2 the hot mixture into the egg yolks, then put that back in pan with the other 1/2 of hot mixture, cook for 1 minute longer.
Remove from heat stir until smooth.
Blend in butter and lemon juice.
Put in cooked pie shell.
Cool.
Put cool whip or meringue on top.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt all ingredients in double boiler; add peanuts.
Stir and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onion and garlic in hot oil in Dutch oven until tender. Add chicken, tomatoes, tomato sauce, chicken broth and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove chicken and let cool.
Add chili powder and oregano to tomato mixture.
Boil, uncovered, until reduced to 3 cups.
Tear chicken into large pieces.
Add chicken, corn and olives; set aside.
Combine cornmeal with 4 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil until thickened.
Remove from heat; let stand for 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Put pecans into blender; grind up fine, then use 1/2 to mix with the preceding.
Form pecans in other half that's left.
Makes 8 to 10 balls.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon in a bowl.
Blend cake mix with applesauce and eggs for two minutes at high speed.
Pour half into pan.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mix, then sliced apples. Add rest of batter.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 38 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl except tortillas and picante sauce.
Put in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Then spread mixture on tortillas.
Roll tortillas, then cut into bite-size pieces.
Use picante sauce
for dipping.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan at 350° for 20 minutes.
Bring cream cheese to room temperature and whip confectioners sugar and cheese thoroughly.
Make Dream Whip following package instructions, then blend Dream Whip and cream cheese mixture together.
Put this mixture on cooled cake.
Put cherries on top of cream mixture and chill.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and let set at room temperature until soft.
Blend Cheddar cheese, cream cheese and pimento together. Add other ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: bacon and cheese potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes; let cool for about 1 hour.
Cut each potato in half and each half in half with a serrated knife.
With your knife, trim some of the potato meat off and save for later use (great for potato salad).
Lay potato skins on a cookie sheet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle potato skins with bacon, shredded Monterey Jack with jalapenos and Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
You can cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate until your party and then pop them in the oven when ready to eat.
Serve hot with Ranch dressing as a dipper.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, sugar, baking powder, and salt. In a separate bowl, combine egg yolks, vanilla and beat slightly. Beat in milk and oil. Add egg mixture to flour mixture. Stir until combined, yet slightly lumpy. In a bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Gently fold beaten egg whites into batter leaving little fluffs of egg whites. Cook according to waffle iron instructions. Top with powdered sugar, optional.

title: fat-free chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar and baking powder.
In separate bowl mix applesauce and cocoa.
Combine with flour mixture.
Beat in milk and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch square or round pan.
On top of batter, sprinkle brown sugar, sugar and cocoa, one at a time. Do not mix!
Pour water over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple dew
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 baking dish or pan with cooking spray. Place each apple slice in a crescent roll (beginning at the wide end, being sure the apple is completely); roll up and place in the baking dish. Melt sugar, oleo and vanilla; pour mixture over apple rolls. Pour the Mountain Dew over the whole thing. Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir shortening just to soften.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add bananas and half the milk.
Mix until all flour is dampened, then beat vigorously for 2 minutes.
Add remaining milk and eggs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: Clean and cube tomatoes, peppers and cuke.
Combine with olives and crumbled Feta cheese, salt and pepper.
In a small jar, shake, until well blended, all remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to recipe and squeeze off all liquid. Mix spinach, stuffing, onions, eggs, cheese, garlic, butter, salt and pepper.
Chill 2 hours or longer.
Roll mixture into about 75 balls, 1-inch in diameter.
Freeze or refrigerate until ready to use.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Heat 20 to 25 minutes on cookie sheet before serving.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to directions.
Rinse well.
Finely chop cucumbers, peppers and tomatoes.
Mix rest of ingredients with spaghetti, tomatoes, cucumbers and peppers.
Toss to mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: snap beans
directions: Combine in pan.
Add a little water and cook until done.

title: spicy chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook pasta as directed. Drain. Return to same pan. Spray skillet with cooking spray. Add chicken. Cook on medium heat 4 to 5 minutes until cooked through. Add Velveeta, soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies, mushrooms and milk. Stir on low heat until Velveeta is melted. Add chicken mixture to pasta. Toss to coat. Spoon into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheddar muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients. Combine remaining ingredients and add to dry mixture. Stir until moistened.
Don't overmix.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Remove from pans immediately. Makes 1 dozen.

title: seven-layer cookies
directions: Melt the margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer the other ingredients in the following order:
cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate, butterscotch, milk and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool and cut in small squares.

title: pineapple cream cheese icebox pie
directions: Drain the pineapple, reserving the juice. Thoroughly beat the cream cheese with the sugar and 2 tablespoons of the reserved pineapple juice, then beat in the pineapple. In a separate bowl, whip the cream until stiff and fold into cheese mixture. Fill pie shell and refrigerate thoroughly. Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Set aside in microwaveproof bowl.
Cut cheese into pieces and add to beef in bowl, mixing well.
Pour tomatoes over mixture and heat in microwave, stirring occasionally until cheese is completely melted.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion till tender.
Just before draining, put frozen vegetables in water to thaw out.
Mix butter and stuffing in large bowl and put in microwave till butter melts.
Mix squash, vegetables, onion, soup and sour cream together.
Make layer of 1/2 stuffing in dish, layer of vegetables mix; top with other half of stuffing mix.

title: grecian curry
directions: Saute onion in olive oil in a heavy skillet.
Saute chicken in onion and oil.
Add remaining ingredients and reduce sauce.
Serve over rice.
Yields 3 servings.

title: mittie's fruit cakes(makes two large cakes)
directions: Mix raisins, currants, figs, dates, citron, nuts and flour in a huge bowl.

title: granny cord's old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl of flour as you would to make biscuits.
Roll out on a board and cut with a round cookie cutter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Heat liquids until very warm.
Add to dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in the rest of the flour to make stiff batter.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Melt butter in skillet on low heat as you begin to slice your vegetables. Slice and add to the following: green pepper, carrots, onions, garlic and celery, in that order, stirring occasionally. Increase heat to medium for 2 to 3 minutes, then add cabbage and greens, marjoram and thyme.

Cook on medium to medium high heat, stirring almost continuously, until greens have wilted but other vegetables are still crisp. Add soy sauce and pepper to taste. Serve with brown or wild rice. Serves 4 (110 calories per serving).

title: one step lasagne
directions: Combine water, sugar, sauce and browned meat.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish with 1 1/2 of the sauce mixture.
Then layer uncooked noodles, 1/2 of the Ricotta or cottage cheese, 1/2 of the Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons of the Parmesan cheese.
Repeat with sauce, noodles and rest of cheeses.
Over that end with sauce, noodles and rest of sauce.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° or until knife will pierce easily.

title: boston clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and pour over vegetables in medium saucepan.
Add enough water to barely cover vegetables.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat until potatoes are tender, about 20 minutes.

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Layer 5 sheets of dough, brushing each layer with melted butter.
Spread 1/3 of ingredients over top layer to 1/4-inch from edges.
Roll like a jelly roll. Cut into pieces with knife.
Repeat procedure for 2 more rolls. Bake at 375°
for 30 to 35 minutes, or freeze to be baked and served later.
Also good served cold.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Microwave ground beef 2 to 3 minutes until brown; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and pepper.

In baking dish, spoon 1/2 cup sauce, alternating layers of noodles, egg mixture, cheese and sauce, forming 2 layers. Heat, covered, for 8 minutes on High, then on Medium-low, covered, for 30 to 32 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: basic roux(for all stews and gumbos)
directions: Heat oil in heavy pot or Dutch oven.
When oil is hot, gradually add flour, stirring continuously until well mixed. Lower flame; continue stirring until chocolate brown.
Remove from pot; set aside.
If roux remains in pot, it will continue to cook and get too dark.

title: aunt sally's all in one dinner
directions: Cooking Time: 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt together and add to cream mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in bananas, nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then on rack.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften.
Blend with other ingredients.
Chill.
Form in a roll or ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and chill again.

title: sparkling fruit compote
directions: Place canned fruit in large bowl.
Mix allspice with plum syrup.
Add to fruit in bowl.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, add apples, bananas and cold ginger ale.

title: butter pecan brownies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg like pie crust.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: boiled crawfish and crabs
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add salt; mix and taste. (If it almost takes your breath, it's enough).
Has to be too salty. Add lemons, onions, celery, garlic, pepper and crab boil (both kinds).
Let come to a hard boil.
Put in crawfish and let come to a boil again.
Time 5 minutes. Add potatoes and corn. After 2 1/2 minutes, turn off flame. Add bag of ice to cool.
Let stand for 20 to 30 minutes.
Boil crabs
10 minutes to boil.
The rest is same as crawfish.
Turn crabs stomach up when taking out of pot; it holds in seasoning.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well, draining the liquid off the whole kernel corn before adding it.
Pour into a casserole and bake at 350°
for 1 hour.

title: zucchini oatmeal muffins
directions: In medium bowl, mix 4 eggs, oil and zucchini.
Add this to flour mixture and stir well until flour is moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake in muffin pans at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: italian vegetable casserole
directions: Save some oleo for top of casserole.
Put butter, celery and onion in microwave until butter melts.
Cook vegetables according to package.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain and mix everything together.
Grease dish and add ingredients.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers (crushed) and remaining oleo on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows together.
Pour over the other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pack into graham cracker box or other container.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and other dry ingredients.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Drop by teaspoon on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cookies are light brown around the edge.

title: garlic bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl and spread on bread.
Wrap in foil and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Unwrap and brown slightly under broiler (can use 1/2 less butter, cheese and much more garlic).

title: mighty minestrone
directions: In medium bowl use a fork to mash cannellini beans in their liquid until smooth; set aside.
In saucepot or Dutch oven, saute cabbage and onion in oil 8 to 10 minutes until cabbage is wilted. Add remaining ingredients and 2 cups water.
Cover and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; recover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: hazel gates southern apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, beaten eggs, spices, flour and melted margarine. Place chopped apples in unbaked crust.
Pour mixture over apples. Do not use top crust. Bake at 325° until done through (45 minutes to 1 hour).

title: spicy good chili
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, 3 hours (uncover during last hour).
Remove garlic and bay leaf.
Good served over spaghetti noodles or rice.

title: southern split pea soup
directions: If you like split pea soup, I would suggest making six times the ingredients listed, eating some and freezing the rest, but still only use one ham bone.

title: pecan candy
directions: Break vanilla wafers in small pieces.
(Do not crush.)
Add broken pieces of pecans to wafers.
Melt butter; add condensed milk and mix.
Pour over vanilla wafers and pecan mixture.
Mix by hand to make sure entire mixture becomes damp.
Mix well!
Line a cake pan (9 x 13-inch) with wax paper and place candy mix into cake pan. Put a piece of wax paper on top and push down hard on candy mixture, spreading evenly throughout pan.
Place in freezer just until hard.
Take out of freezer to thaw slightly before serving. Keep candy cold in refrigerator.
Candy will tend to crumble when left out too long.

title: red rice
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet until crisp; remove bacon reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Cook onion in drippings over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Add bacon, tomato and remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes. Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 1-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: raddicchio, arugula and endive salad
directions: Tear endive, arugula and raddicchio into bite size pieces. Whisk oil, vinegar, mustard, garlic, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Serve after tossing.
Serves 4.

title: tricia's cheese ball
directions: Combine softened and chunked cream cheese, grated Cheddar and Parmesan in food processor.
Add all other ingredients and enough milk to thin to desired consistency.
If it's real thick, just keep adding milk until it is processed to a good, thick, creamy mixture.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, Italian dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Chill and serve.
Makes 4 servings.
Best when chilled overnight.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and soda in large bowl.
Add oil, vanilla and beaten eggs and mix well.
Batter will be stiff.
Stir in apples.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Spoon into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes.
Place cake on serving plate.

title: oyster stew
directions: Brown onion lightly in skillet.
Add celery and heat through. Place in top of 2-quart double boiler.
Add milk and oysters.
Heat in double boiler 15 minutes or until oysters curl.
Add crumbled crackers and paprika.
Heat 5 minutes more.
Serve with saltines. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper.
May add 1/2 teaspoon savory for a nice flavor addition.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Cook chicken breasts and slice.
Arrange broccoli in bottom of 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Lay chicken slices on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Top with grated cheese.
Mix bread crumbs with butter and spread on top of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: tangy chicken legs
directions: In saucepan, combine the first six ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Brush over cooked chicken.
Yield: 8 servings (1 1/2 cups barbecue sauce).

title: old-fashioned seafoam
directions: Cook brown sugar, water and vinegar until the syrup forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water.
Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites.
Work in 1/2 cup of nuts and vanilla.
Drop in small pieces on waxed paper.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Note:
Need child's sand bucket and shovel.

title: tea cakes
directions: Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Cut margarine into flour mixture.
Beat together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
Put dough in refrigerator at least 2 hours.
Roll out 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes. Bake on greased cookie sheet 6 to 7 minutes at 325°.

title: chewy walnut squares
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Stir together egg, brown sugar and vanilla.
Quickly stir in flour, baking soda and salt.
Add walnuts.
Spread in pan and bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes. Cookies should be soft in center when taken from oven.
Leave in pan.
Cut into 2-inch squares or smaller.

title: jazzy berry java
directions: Puree frozen raspberries, sugar, and water in a blender cup. Strain mixture into a large mixing bowl.
Add coffee and half-and-half.
Blend well.
Ladle into 12 oz. glasses, partially filled with cracked ice.
Top with whipped cream, mint sprigs, and whole raspberries.
Makes 10 servings.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Beat egg untill fluffy. Mix in remaining ingredients, until smooth. For thinner pancakes, add 1\4 cup Milk.
Grease heated griddle. For each pancake, pour 3 tbsp. of batter. Cook until puffed and dry around edges. Turn and cook other side. Makes 9 four inch pancakes.

title: salmon macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Drain salmon, reserving liquid and flake it.
Add milk to salmon liquid to make 2 cups.
Saute onion in margarine.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and salmon liquid.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.

title: ziti and shrimp
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions.
Drain well, place in a large serving dish, cover with foil and keep warm.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add broccoli, pepper, onions and oregano.
Cover and cook for 8 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in the shrimp, mandarin peel, garlic, salt and ginger.
Cook uncovered for 4 to 6 minutes or until shrimp is bright pink.
Stir in the half and half, bring to a boil, reduce heat, cook covered for 2 minutes.
Pour sauce over ziti, toss well.
Place well drained mandarins over top, serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple pies
directions: Add lemon juice to condensed milk.
Next, add drained pineapple, then pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into 2 prepared graham cracker crusts and chill.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini. Drain.
Place cooked linguini in a large bowl. Add Salad Supreme, tomato, cucumber and pepper.
Add salad dressings.
Mix well. Chill for 6 to 8 hours.

title: cereal bars
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan; set aside.
In medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add marshmallows and cook until melted, stirring frequently.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Saute onion in oleo; add mushroom soup, hominy and pepper. Put in baking dish with cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Blend in dry ingredients. Finally, stir in bananas and raisins.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 55 minutes at 325°.

title: caramel pie
directions: Remove label from condensed milk and put entire unopened can in a large saucepan.
Cover with cold water.
Over high heat, bring the water to a boil.
Reduce heat and continue boiling for 3 hours.
Check periodically to see that water covers the can entirely.
Remove can and cool unopened for 20 minutes.
Open can and spread caramelized milk in the bottom of the pie crust.
Over the caramel sprinkle 3/4 cup of the chopped pecans.
Pat the pecans into the caramel with open hand.
Over the caramel and pecans, spread the whipped topping.
Garnish with remaining pecans.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs together.
Sift flour and cinnamon together.
Fold in.
Fold in other ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Let sit in pan for 10 minutes; then turn out. Make a glaze of powdered sugar and water, thin enough for it to run down the sides of cake.

title: swiss french bread
directions: Mix the margarine, onion, dry mustard and poppy seed.
Slice and butter bread.
Put cheese between slices of bread.
Pour mixture over bread. Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in dressing. Cook 15 minutes in microwave. Grill.

title: sweet and sour cabbage salad
directions: Massage shredded cabbage with salt. Add oil, vinegar, sugar, mayonnaise and crushed pineapple. Mix well. Serve chilled.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, Cool Whip and confectioners sugar.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Put pie filling on top. Refrigerate for 1 hour and serve.

title: mom kahn's elbows and chopped meat
directions: Cook and drain elbow macaroni.
In a pan saute onion and pepper until tender.
Add and brown meat.
Add tomatoes, water and spices to taste.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat.
Simmer for 1 hour covered.
Uncover and cook on high to dry out.
Kidney beans may be added if desired.

title: weight watcher's ambrosia
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate in covered dish.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and add green chilies and onion; season with salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
In microwave, stir together soups, enchilada sauce and evaporated milk.
Dip corn tortillas in grease for a second to warm.
Spray dish with Pam and tear corn tortillas up and cover bottom of dish.
Then add a layer of meat, a layer of soup and a layer of cheese.
Start over with tortillas and add all the layers again.
Top off with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° until bubbly.

title: karla's chili
directions: In a large pan, brown hamburger with onion and Worcestershire sauce.
After brown, drain grease.
Add chili powder, tomato juice, salt, brown sugar and chili beans. Simmer all day!
One hour before serving, add spaghetti or macaroni.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream the cheese, NutraSweet (or powdered sugar) and milk until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and beat until smooth. Fold whipped topping into peanut butter mixture and pour into pie crusts.
Garnish with chopped peanuts and chill five to six hours or overnight.
(This pie freezes good and will last 2 or 3 months.)

title: no cook coconut pie
directions: Beat pudding mix, milk and extract on low speed for 2 minutes, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in coconut.
Pour into graham cracker crust and sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Chill.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer in casserole dish.
Top with crumbled Cheez-Its.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apricot delight
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add 1 cup juice and chill until slightly set.
Add cut up fruit and marshmallows.
Put in 11 x 9 x 2-inch dish. When set, add topping and cover with cheese.

title: artichoke casserole
directions: Drain and quarter artichokes.
Wash, dry, slice and saute mushrooms in margarine.
Mix mayonnaise, cheeses and garlic powder.
Layer artichokes, mushrooms and cheese mixtures in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan and bread crumbs. Add a dash of paprika if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until bubbling.

title: pumpkin pecan cake
directions: In large bowl, combine
first
ingredients.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Fold
in chopped pecans.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan, at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for
10 to 15 minutes; turn out on wire
rack to complete
cooling.
Serve
with
whipped
cream topping.
Good at Thanksgiving!

title: texas caviar
directions: Combine in a very large bowl and marinate for 24 hours before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
When cooled, add strawberries. Chill until slightly thick.
Whip cream and fold in strawberry mixture.
In 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan, place 1/2 cake broken in chunks.
Pour 1/2 of the gelatin mixture over the cake.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours before serving.

title: cherry, pineapple cake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with cherries.
Next, layer pineapple.
Next, layer coconut.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Slice butter in pats and lay on top.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: french onion beef roast(slow cooker)
directions: Preheat slow cooker on high for a few minutes.
Dredge meat in flour.
Saute roast on each side, about 4 minutes.
Place meat in slow cooker and reduce heat to low.
Reduce heat in saute pan; stir in 2 Tbsp. flour and stir to a smooth paste (about 1 minute). Add soup mix and mushrooms and return to boil.
Pour over roast. Simmer 8 - 10 hours.

title: grandma newton's fruit cobbler
directions: Heat 1 quart of fruit; sweeten to taste.
Turn oven to 350°. Melt 1/4 cup margarine in pan until bubbling.
Mix together in bowl all remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into bubbling margarine, then pour hot fruit over batter.
Bake until done, approximately 1/2 hour or until batter is brown.

title: grammy's super waffles
