directions: Mix first 5 ingredients (add enough flour to make a rather stiff batter).
When ready to bake, add soda and beat hard for a few minutes.

title: mushrooms with wild rice
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and cook until tender, about 1 hour.
Place onion, celery and 1/4 cup of water in saucepan.
Cook and stir for several minutes until vegetables soften slightly. Add button, shiitake and oyster mushrooms.
Cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes.
Gently stir in cooked rice, enoki mushrooms, snow peas, red pepper and seasonings.
Cook over low heat for 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Put in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Combine corn meal, flour and salt.
Add milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Coat with additional flour.
Dip into corn meal mixture. Fry a few at a time in deep hot oil until golden brown.

title: orange marmalade chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased baking pan and cover with marmalade. Sprinkle onion soup over marmalade and then pour Italian dressing over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. The marmalade sauce is great over rice or potatoes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix egg yolks; add milk and lemon juice.
Pour into pie shell. Beat cream of tartar and egg whites until foamy.
Spread and seal over.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Place all ingredients in processor or blender.
Mix slightly. Serve immediately.
May be doubled or tripled.

title: one minute fudge icing
directions: In a saucepan, combine ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Beat until starts to thicken.
Spread over cake.
Top with chopped nuts (optional).

title: oatmeal sesame rolls
directions: In a saucepan, heat milk to very warm.
Add margarine, sugar and salt.
Cook to lukewarm.
Add whole wheat flour and yeast in a larger bowl.
Add sour cream, oatmeal and one egg; mix well.
Stir in flour and mix until you have a soft dough.
Knead until smooth. Place in a greased bowl, turn and cover.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down.
Divide into 18 pieces.
Roll each to rope shape about 3/4-inch thick.
Beginning at centers form a loose swirl and tuck end under.
Let rise until doubled again.
Brush with 1 beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until browned.

title: brandy
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Mix 2 teaspoons yeast, 2 teaspoons sugar and 1 cup warm water together.
Then add to water and sugar mixture.
Add fruit and cover.
Let sit 6 weeks; then fill jars to top.
Leave room for expanding.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine brown sugar, corn syrup, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Beat well.
Stir in morsels, nuts, oats, raisins and orange rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: mutton chops
directions: Cook lamb chops in 2-3 cups of water along with turmeric and salt until tender.
While there is still water left in the meat, add garlic paste, cumin powder, cayenne pepper and cilantro paste and cook until the gravy gets soaked and the flavor combines with the meat.

title: salmon stew
directions: Boil potatoes, onions, salt and pepper with fatback until potatoes are done.
Add salmon and cook an additional 5 to 10 minutes; serve.

title: old fashioned irish stew
directions: Cut 4 potatoes in slices and quarter the rest.
Layer potato slices in a baking dish.
Add half of the onion rings and the meat. Season with salt, pepper and thyme.
Add the remaining onions, carrots and potatoes in the pan.
Season.
Pour in 2 cups of water. Cover the pan with aluminum foil and place a lid on top.
Cook in oven at 350° for about 2 1/2 hours.
The last 15 minutes of cooking, remove cover to lightly brown.
Serve.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all liquids and rice.
Pour 1/2 mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with uncooked chicken.
Pour rest of mixture on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and almonds.
Bake, uncovered, at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: german chocolate caramel cake
directions: Bake the cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While still warm, poke holes with a wooden spoon handle about every 1 to 2-inches apart. Pour and spread on sweetened condensed milk. Spoon on caramel ice cream topping. When cool, spread on container of Cool Whip and sprinkle with 1/4 cup chopped pecans.

title: ground meat casserole - t.v. channel 40
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Mix 4 soups together.
Layer in order: meat, veggies, soup mixture, Tater Tots.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ding bats
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and cook on low heat until nice and smooth.
Remove from stove and add vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Cool 5 minutes; shape into small balls with your hands. Roll in chopped nuts or coconut.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together; form into 2 balls.
Roll in chopped nuts. Refrigerate.

title: baked ice cream pie in cocoa crust
directions: Pack ice cream firmly into cooled pie crust.
If not serving immediately, wrap and place in freezer until ready to serve.
Just before serving, make meringue by beating egg whites with salt until definite peaks form when beater is lifted.
Gradually beat in cream of tartar and sugar until meringue is very stiff.
Add vanilla. Pile meringue tightly over ice cream making sure meringue touches pie crust all the way around.
Bake in a very hot 450° oven for 3 minutes or until meringue is delicately browned.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8-inch deep pie or 9-inch shallow pie.

title: 3 layer jell-o salad
directions: 1st Layer: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 1 cup hot water. Add pear juice (approximately 1 cup). Place pears in Jell-O and chill.

title: italian beef
directions: Roast meat and all ingredients in 350° oven for 3 plus hours or until tender.
Remove meat, cool slightly and shred into cooking broth.
If more au jus is needed, add partial can of beef broth.
Serve over French bread.

title: no fat no mess muffins
directions: Smash 3 good sized bananas in a mixing bowl.
Add the vanilla, oatmeal and oat bran (or you can just use oatmeal).
Mix together and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on how hard you want them.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put dry rice in baking dish.
Pour water and margarine over rice.
Lay chicken pieces (seasoned to taste) on top of rice.
Top with cream of chicken soup.
Cover and bake 1 hour or until chicken is done at 375°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in bottom of 8 x 8 Pyrex (glass) bowl. In a small mixing bowl, mix butter, sugar and flour together. Mixture should be crumbly. Sprinkle over apples. Add cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: jule kaga(christmas bread)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Pour scalded milk over butter.
When lukewarm, add yeast and sugar.
Add 1/2 of flour and salt.
Beat well for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, beating thoroughly.
Add fruit and remaining flour.
Knead.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Stir cream cheese until well softened.
Blend in 1/2 milk until mixture is very smooth.
Add remaining 1/2 milk and pudding mix.
Beat with electric mixer until well blended.
Pour into pan.
Chill.
Top with cherry or strawberry pie filling.

title: german pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs in bowl.
Add flour and milk. Beat until smooth, but don't overbeat.
Melt butter in bottom of cooking pan.
Pour butter in pan.
Bake at 425° on middle shelf for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and green pepper in margarine.
Add pimento, soup and cream cheese.
Heat slowly until blended.
Add rice, shrimp and crab meat.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place crushed crackers on top the last 10 minutes of baking time.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl.
Add sugar and flour and mix well.
Put oleo in 1/2 cup of hot water for a few minutes, then add to other mixture.
Stir in 3/4 cup coconut and mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle remaining coconut on top of pie.
Bake at 325° until pie is firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift ingredients together. Mix with the wet ingredients. Add 1/2 cup nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done. Makes 2 large loaves.

title: lynn's lasagna(not for low-fat diets!)
directions: You will need a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole or glass cake pan. Brown ground beef; drain and crumble.
Boil noodles and drain. Pour small layer of Prego into pan.
Add small layer of crumbled beef.
Mix Ricotta and sour cream together to spread or use teaspoon to drop in rows.
Add light layer of Mozzarella.
Add layer of noodles.
Add layer of sauce.
Continue layer by layer sauce, beef, Ricotta, sour cream and cheese.
End with generous layer of Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Happy eating.

title: water chestnut hors d'oeuvres
directions: Wrap each water chestnut in 1/2 strip of bacon and secure with toothpick.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until bacon is done. Remove to chafing dish.
In a small saucepan, combine remaining ingredients over low heat to make sauce.
Pour over chestnuts. Keep warm.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Blend broth into soup. Add all other ingredients, except almonds. Pour into 2-quart casserole. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes. Just before serving, sprinkle with almonds.

title: chewy butterscotch bars
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add sugar and bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Drop in eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in the nuts.
Pour into the pan (bottom rubbed with butter).
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: frozen creamy corn
directions: Place all ingredients in a saucepan and stir to blend.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently until mixture comes to a boil.
Serves 6.

title: harvest loaf cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, beating well. Stir together flour, salt, soda and spices. Add to butter mixture; alternate with pumpkin, beginning and ending with dry ingredients and beating well after each addition. Stir in chocolate chips and 3/4 cup walnuts. Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle with walnuts. Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.

title: petite cheesecakes
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together. Add eggs, one at a time. Beat until light and fluffy. Line cupcake tins with double paper liners. Place vanilla wafers in the bottom of each. Add cream cheese mixture to each liner so it is 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool. Top with pie filling. Chill until ready to serve. Top with whipped cream if desired. Serves 42.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour & mix with baking powder, soda & salt. Cream shortening & sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beat well after each egg. Add bananas with 1/4 of flour mixture at a time, beat well. Stir in nuts. Turn into well greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 min. Cool on rack before slicing.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish mix soup, milk, pepper, broccoli, and 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot. Stir sprinkle remaining onions over broccoli mixture.
Bake additional 5 minutes or until onions are golden.
Can use larger can of French's onions if desired.

title: summer herbed beans
directions: Precook beans in a small amount of boiling water for 4 minutes; drain.
In a small dish combine butter (melted), basil, dill, salt and pepper; set aside.
Pour olive oil into large skillet (add more oil if necessary).
Heat over medium-high heat. Add partially cooked beans; stir-fry about 3 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Add tomato wedges and butter herb sauce; heat through.
Put in serving dish and sprinkle with Feta cheese.

title: cream cheese crabmeat mold
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water; let stand 1 minute.
Heat soup in saucepan; add gelatin mixture to soup.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly until gelatin dissolves and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Remove from heat.
Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise; mix well at medium speed of electric mixer.
Add cream cheese topping to soup mixture.
Stir in celery and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into slightly oiled 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine all.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers while hot.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Toast sunflower seeds and almonds.
Crush noodles; shred cabbage and toss.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine condensed soup, milk and sherry. Bring just to boiling. Add margarine or butter if desired. Reduce heat. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes, stirring often. Chop shrimp if desired. Add shrimp to mixture; return to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 to 2 minutes more or until shrimp are just cooked through. To serve, ladle into individual serving bowls. Garnish with cilantro sprigs if desired. Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and cream.
Add flour and milk alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: banana-zucchini bread
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Blend in sugar and oil.
Add bananas and mix well.
Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt; stir into egg mixture.
Stir in zucchini and pecans just until combined.
Pour into two greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pudding and 1 1/4 cups milk in large saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until thick and comes to full boil.
Stir constantly with whisk.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pumpkin and spices, using the whisk.
Cook and stir on medium heat until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 20 minutes or until almost cool.
Stir constantly.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water. Combine milk, sugar, shortening, salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add softened yeast and egg.
Gradually stir in flour to form soft dough.
Beat vigorously;
cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 3 hours.
Roll 1/2 of the dough on lightly floured surface to rectangle, 1/4 inch thick.
Brush with 4 Tbsp. margarine.
Sprinkle with mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 3 tsp. cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll, seal edges, cut in one inch slices, place in greased baking pan.
Do the same with rest of dough.
Cover and let rise until double. Bake in moderate oven 375 degrees for 25 minutes.
Makes 24 rolls. Remove from pan.
Cool.
Frost with confectioners icing.

title: chocolate ice cream sauce
directions: Cook in saucepan the grated chocolate, sugar, cornstarch and milk.
When it is thickened, add oleo, vanilla and salt.

title: cake-mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and roll into small balls. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Make around 4 dozen cookies.

title: quick cottage cheese salad
directions: Stir Jell-O into cottage cheese dry.
Add other ingredients. Other flavors of Jell-O can be used too and chopped sliced peaches or fruit cocktail can be used.

title: rice casserole
directions: Prepare Hamburger Helper according to instructions on box. Then pour 1/2 of hamburger in casserole dish. Top with cheese and taco sauce and remaining hamburger, cheese and taco sauce. Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: julie's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with foil, allowing ends to hang over edge.
Break each graham cracker into four rectangles.
Place graham crackers in a single layer in foil-lined pan; set aside.
In a medium saucepan over medium heat, bring margarine and sugar to a boil and boil for 1 minute.
Pour over graham crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake for 10 minutes or until bubbly and topping is no longer clear.
For easier removal of cookies, let them sit for a minute or so after taking pan out of oven.
Carefully lift 2 to 3 rectangles out at a time with a spatula.
Place on wire racks to cool.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with stuffing and seasoning packet. Boil zucchini and carrots in water 2 to 3 minutes. Drain. Mix all ingredients together and place in baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: wild rice and sausage casserole
directions: Cook wild rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile brown sausage and then stir in onions and mushrooms and simmer for 15 minutes.
Mix in soup and Milnot.
Put into casserole dish and top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: apple nut muffins
directions: Grease 12 medium muffin cups.
Mix cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar for sprinkling tops.
In a bowl beat eggs with juice, oil and vanilla.
Stir in flour, 1/4 cup sugar, baking powder and salt just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy).
Stir in nuts and apple.
Fill prepared muffin cups.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump can of crushed pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan.
Even it out.
Put cherry pie filling on top of the pineapple.
Dump 1 dry yellow cake mix on top of that.
Even cake mix out with fork.
Pat top of cake mix with 1 stick butter or oleo.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg nog
directions: In saucepan, combine well beaten eggs, condensed milk, vanilla and salt. Mix until well blended. Cook on medium-low heat. Gradually add milk and then gently fold in whipped cream. Cook until mixture is hot. Pour in punch bowl or serve in cups. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Makes 2 quarts.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Combine ingredients in a deep, narrow bottom bowl.
Beat to blend, then whip at high speed to soft peaks, 4 to 6 minutes. Frosts 8 to 9-inch layer cake.
Store frosted cake in refrigerator.

title: banana split salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and crushed pineapple.
Divide mixture in half and mix lime jello in half and orange jello in other half.
Cut bananas in halves vertically.
Place 1 scoop of each flavor cottage cheese on bananas.
Sprinkle with pecans. Serves 12.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut florets off broccoli.
Add cheese to the amount you'd like.
Crumble bacon and add to mixture, along with onion.
Mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli mixture and mix thoroughly.

title: 3 bean hot dish
directions: In skillet, brown diced bacon.
Drain and save 3 tablespoons of fat.
In pan, brown together hamburger and onion.
In casserole dish, mix together the bacon, hamburger and onion mixture and beans.
In a small bowl, mix together brown sugar, catsup, prepared mustard, bacon fat and salt and pepper.
Mix this in with bean mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cabbage roll casserole
directions: Brown ground
beef
and
onion, then combine 1/4 cup of rice. Cut
cabbage.
Place
on bottom of casserole.	Add beef and rice mixture.
Cover with remaining cabbage.
Dilute 1 can of tomato
soup
with	1
can of water.
Pour over top. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered.

title: peach streusel crunch pie
directions: Spread pie filling in a pastry lined pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over filling.
After putting pie in convection-aire oven, place a 10-inch round of aluminum foil lightly over top of pie.
Bake until hot and bubbly.
Remove foil the last 5 to 10 minutes of baking.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Put cream and sugar in ice box to cool while mixing together Eagle Brand, lemon juice, pineapple and pecans.
Add the whipping cream mixture to the other.
Put in crusts.
Keep refrigerated until all is eaten.

title: apple bread
directions: Cream the sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Combine the remaining ingredients with the creamed mixture.
The batter will be real stiff.
Grease bread pans heavily.
Pour batter in pans and sprinkle sugar on the batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: candy kisses cookies
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except candy.
Mix on low speed until dough forms.
Shape in balls; roll each in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Top each cookie with candy while warm.

title: chocolate chip ice cream
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites until stiff.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks to the egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients
to the egg mixture.
Blend and freeze in electric freezer.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix about half of the flour, all of the brown sugar, shortening, molasses, egg, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium to high speed until combined.
Beat or stir in remaining flour.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Roll balls in the granulated sugar to coat.
Place balls two inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for about 8 - 10 minutes or until edges are set and tops are cracked.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: ham and cheese potato bake
directions: Layer half the potatoes and half the carrots in a 2-quart casserole.
Stir together cubed ham, condensed mushroom soup, the 3/4 cup shredded cheese, milk, instant minced onion and pepper. Pour half the ham mixture over potatoes and carrots in casserole. Repeat layers.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix and roll into balls.
Cook in oven with foil on top until done.

title: vegetable soup burgundy
directions: Simmer carrots 15 minutes in 1 1/2-quarts water.
Add onions and simmer 10 minutes.
Add celery and simmer 10 minutes, then add tomatoes, bouillon and prepared Lawry's Burgundy Wine Sauce Mix and simmer 5 minutes more.
This makes about 1 gallon of soup. Beef chunks can be added to make a Vegetable Beef Soup Burgundy.

title: layered tortilla pie
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add tomato sauce, olives, chili powder, salt and pepper.
In a round 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of tortillas, meat, sauce and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese over top.
Pour water at edge of casserole bottom.
Cover and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Uncover, let stand 5 minutes, cut into wedges.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken and broccoli rice casserole
directions: Simmer onions and mushrooms
in
a
large
skillet with butter until tender.
Stir
in
rice,
chicken,
broccoli
and soup. Pour into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Prepare container or freezer jars and lids according to manufacturer's instructions.
Crush strawberries.
Stir in lemon juice.
Stir sugar into berry mixture and let stand 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine water and pectin in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil and then boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add to berry mixture, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Carefully ladle into can or freezer jars, leaving 1/2-inch of headspace.
Adjust caps.
Let stand at room temperature.
Makes about 5 (8 ounce) jars.

title: manicotti parmigiana
directions: In saucepan, combine spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, garlic spread and salt.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Cook manicotti. Brown meat and green peppers; remove from heat and drain off fat. Stir in diced Mozzarella cheese and stuff tubes.
Pour 3/4 of the sauce in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange stuffed manicotti over sauce.
Put remaining sauce over manicotti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mint taffy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and honey in saucepan; cook until sugar is dissolved, stirring constantly.
Add cream of tartar and boil for 20 minutes.
Add vanilla, butter and peppermint.
Return to boil; pour into buttered pan.
Cool and pull until smooth; cut into squares.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a casserole dish, spread refried beans.
Then pour jar of salsa over refried beans.
Spread can of diced green chiles over salsa.
Grate both pounds of cheese; sprinkle over diced green chiles.
Sprinkle diced green onions and sliced olives over the top.
Bake at 325° for approximately 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: mound cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Let cool; cut into 2 layers. Melt sugar, milk, margarine, vanilla and marshmallows.
After melted, add coconut; pour over bottom layer.
Stack top layer on, then frost with chocolate frosting.

title: out of this world pork chops
directions: Dip chops in beaten egg, then in Italian bread crumbs.
In a skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Place browned chops in a casserole with the milk and cover.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Yum, yum!

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Stir together the flour, cocoa, baking soda, sugar and salt. Add the rest; mix by hand.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan for 45 minutes or until done at 325°.

title: layered salad
directions: If using frozen peas, heat 10 minutes; if in can, use as is. Cook bacon and set aside.
Place layer of lettuce (using all), layer of carrots, layer of peas (all), layer of dressing, all of chopped mixture, all of water chestnuts and all of cheese.
Place all of shredded bacon on top and cover with Saran Wrap.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat water, butter, sugar and salt to boiling point, then add flour.
Stir vigorously and cook until batter leaves side of pan and follows spoon.
Remove from stove.
While still hot, add eggs one at a time and beat well after each egg, then drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet 2 inches apart.
When cold, cut with sharp knife and fill with cream filling.
Bake 50 minutes (at 425° for first 15 minutes, then at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes longer). Serves 18.

title: red hot punch
directions: Make the strong tea and melt the red hot candies in it.
Put the cloves in a small piece of cheesecloth.
Put in warm tea mix. Let set about 1 hour, or until somewhat cool.
Add juices and extract, then water.
Sugar to taste (Usually you do not need to add any sugar.)
Refrigerate.
Warm it as you need it.
Serve hot. Serves 24.

title: spanish casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Pour
off	grease.
Add bell pepper, mushrooms, onion, corn, tomato juice, olives and chili powder. Add cooked noodles to beef mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 375° oven. Serve with green or mixed salad and hot cornbread.

title: daddy's featherlight pancakes
directions: Mix egg and sugar.
Add oil.
Add vanilla, then milk.
Combine together all dry ingredients.
Fold wet and dry mixes together. If it's too thick, add milk.
Cook and enjoy!

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; add oranges and mix by hand.
Pour into 3 greased and floured layer cake pans.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour.
Roll into little balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fingers dipped in egg white.
Put oven at 350°.
Bake for 12 minutes.

title: stir-fry pie
directions: Cook carrot in microwave a few minutes.
Put all in deep Pyrex pan.
Mix milk, eggs and Bisquick in blender; pour over veggies.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes in a 400° oven.
Last 5 minutes, top with cheese.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before cutting.

title: girl scout punch
directions: Blend all ingredients together with enough water to make 2 gallons.

title: layered cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage, placing half of it in a bowl. Reserve the other half. Sprinkle chopped onion over cabbage. Sprinkle chopped green pepper over onion. Top with remaining cabbage. Sprinkle sugar over the top of cabbage. Do not stir. Bring oil, vinegar, salt and celery seed to a full boil and pour this hot mixture over the cabbage mixture. Do not stir! Cover container and place in refrigerator overnight. Next day, stir well. This will keep for 10 days or longer in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients together and set aside.
Melt remaining ingredients together over low heat.
Add nuts and vanilla last.
Stir well and pat 2/3 of oat mixture in bottom of baking pan.
Spread chocolate mixture over dough.
Dot remaining oat mixture over chocolate filling.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in 1 x 2-inch squares.
Do not overwork dough.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine carrots with onions and peppers.
Blend other ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put bread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch dish; add sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over.
Cover with foil and chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: kentucky fried style chicken
directions: Prepare soup mix.
Dip chicken in soup.
Roll in mixture of flour and Italian dressing.
Melt margarine in bottom of baking dish.
Place chicken in pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple fritters
directions: Peel and chop apples.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon in a bowl.
Add egg, oil and milk; mix well.
Stir in apples.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Fry until brown and drain on paper towels.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown and drain meat, add garlic, parsley, basil, tomatoes and paste. Simmer for one hour. Cook and drain noodles. Combine cottage cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, parsley and parmesan. In a 9x13 pan put 3 noodle lengthwise. Spread 1/2 cottage cheese mixture cover with mozzarella then cover with 1/2 meat mixture. Repeat. place last 3 noodles on top and cover with mozzarella. Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 15 x 10-inch pan with Pam. Skin and remove fat from chicken.
Dip chicken in milk; coat with dry ingredients.
Place in pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until juice runs clear when pierced with fork.

title: meat potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Peel potatoes and slice.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, layer hamburger, potatoes and onion.
Pour soup mixture (1/2 cup milk and soup) over top and down sides.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve hot.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small, bite-sized pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Reserve the trunk as you will need something to store pieces in.
You will need enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over open fire for about 4 weeks.
Keep heat at approximately 365°. This will serve about 3,800 people.
If more are expected, the 2 rabbits may be added.
Do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to fine hare in their stew.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in oleo until transparent.
Crumble corn bread; add sage, salt and pepper.
Mix beaten eggs with soups and broth.
Stir ingredients together and fold in chopped chicken. Put in crock-pot.
Cook on high 45 minutes.
Turn on low (stir mixture) and continue cooking 4 to 6 hours.

title: party potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, soups, seasonings and sour cream in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt, flour and cornstarch; mix well.
Slowly add milk, mixing well.
Cook over medium heat in heavy saucepan, stirring to prevent scorching and lumping.
When mixture thickens, add oleo and vanilla.
Then slowly add beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick and cool a few minutes and pour into a baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and sprinkle coconut on top.
Brown in slow oven.

title: chocolate nut squares
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with buttered foil; set aside.
Melt both chips with shortening in heavy small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Spoon half the chocolate mixture into prepared pan, spreading evenly over bottom and 1/4 inch up sides of pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Meanwhile, combine caramels, butter and milk in heavy medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture is smooth, stir in pecans.
Cool to lukewarm.
Spread caramel mixture evenly over chocolate in pan. Remelt remaining chocolate mixture over very low heat.
Spread over caramel layer.
Refrigerate until almost firm.
Cut into squares. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken breasts diane(microwave)
directions: Place chicken breasts between sheets of waxed paper.
Pound with mallet.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In microwave-safe dish, melt butter and mix with oil.
Place chicken breasts in dish; turn to coat on both sides.
Microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Let rest 1 minute.
Turn and microwave 3 minutes on High until chicken is done.
Set aside.

title: coach stuker's marinated grilled flank steak
directions: Score the meat several times on each side.
The cuts should be 1/4-inch across the grain.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Then mix.
Then add flour, soda and salt.

title: unstuffed "stuffed" cabbage
directions: Mix meat with eggs, rice and sugar.
Season with cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Form into balls.
To make sauce, saute onion in oil until golden.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 jar of water from tomato sauce jar, sauerkraut, brown sugar and raisins.
Heat mixture.
Should be sweet and sour.
Shred cabbage or cut into thin strips eliminating any hard-veined parts.
Pour some of sauce on bottom of roasting pan.
Layer half the shredded cabbage over sauce.
Place meat balls on top of cabbage, cover with remaining cabbage and pour on remaining sauce.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Lower heat to 275° and bake for 1 more hour.

title: vi's baked beans
directions: Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: mint brownies
directions: Bake brownies according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not overbake.
Cool.

title: strawberry cloud pie
directions: Line bottom and side of a 9-inch pie plate with ladyfinger halves, split sides up.
Set aside.
In large bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Refrigerate until thickened but not set, 40 to 50 minutes.
Add whipped topping and confectioners sugar, stirring with wire whisk or fork to blend. Refrigerate until almost set, 30 to 40 minutes.
Fold in sliced strawberries.
Spoon high into ladyfinger crust.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with strawberries.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Thaw strawberries.
Measure 1/2 cup and drain (save for icing).
Mix together cake mix, jello and flour.
Add oil and remaining strawberries (juice and all).
After all ingredients are mixed, pour batter into 3 greased 8-inch pans.
Bake at 325° until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Beat egg; add sugar to egg, then add egg mixture to melted butter.
Add dates and nuts.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until dates soften.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well.
Let cool long enough to roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar or coconut.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon slowly in a Dutch oven until fat begins to fry out. Add minced onion and cook over low heat until onion turns yellow.
Add liquid from the 2 cans of clams, potatoes and boiling water.
Cook until potatoes are tender, about 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add clams, milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread mix, Mexican cornbread mix, egg and milk together and pour into a 12 muffin pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes. Crumble into a large bowl.

title: italian cream cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Separate eggs and beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside. Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk; add alternately with flour.
Beat well.
Add coconut, nuts and extracts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans, using 2 cups batter for each pan. Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool completely, then frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: baked egg custard
directions: Combine the egg substitute or eggs and the sugar in a large bowl and stir with a wire whisk until the sugar is dissolved. Whisk in the remaining ingredients.

title: mother's light rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Put yeast in warm water.
Add sugar and ingredients.
Form into ball; let rise, then make out rolls in pan and let rise again.
Bake in hot oven at 400° until brown.

title: pickling pig cake
directions: Beat really well.
Bake at 350° or according to box.

title: apple bread
directions: Combine all of ingredients.
Place in greased loaf pans; bake around 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: heavenly onions
directions: The day before you plan to serve this dish, saute onions and mushrooms in butter.
Arrange a layer of onions and mushrooms in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Swiss cheese, then add layer of bread and pour over all a mixture of soup, milk, salt, pepper and soy sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Blend liquid ingredients with a blender or hand mixer.

title: canadian cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in blender to chop fine.
Then simmer in 2 tablespoons butter until tender.
Stir in flour, milk, chicken broth and paprika.
Cook until bubbly.
Add cheese, a little at a time.
Simmer; do not boil.
Ready when all blended. Makes 8 cups.

title: iris' red velvet cake with frosting
directions: Blend together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add sugar and then eggs, buttermilk, cocoa, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix well; then add food coloring.
Pour evenly into 3 greased and floured round cake pans.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add dry Jell-O, cottage cheese and Cool Whip. Whip and let set for 4 hours.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs one at a time while beating. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add this mixture alternately with 1 cup buttermilk.
Add coconut flavoring and Angel Flake coconut; stir well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin apple streusel muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine first five ingredients; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, pumpkin and oil.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients; stir just until moistened.
Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into greased or paper-lined muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Sprinkle streusel topping over batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 18 muffins or 36 to 40 mini-muffins.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: round deer steak
directions: Take your round deer steak and cut into strips.
Add your 1/2 cup of Dale's steak seasoning and the Montreal steak seasoning (sprinkle to your liking).
Let marinate for at least 2 hours. Then melt your butter or margarine and simmer strips with bell pepper and onion for about 1 hour.
(Cover your skillet.)

title: broccoli dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let set overnight.
Serve with Hawaiian bread.

title: paella
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry; remove and discard skin.
Spray a Dutch oven with spray coating; add onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add chicken pieces, chicken broth, tomatoes (undrained), thyme, saffron and ground red pepper.
Bring to boiling, then reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in rice and cover and simmer for another 15 minutes or until rice is nearly tender.
Stir in green or red pepper strips, shrimp and peas.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until rice and chicken are tender and shrimp turn pink.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green pepper casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: easy chili beans
directions: Brown burger and drain grease.
Add other ingredients and simmer on low until onion is tender.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Cream together eggs, oleo, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix sugars, salt, baking powder and flour; add slowly to peanut butter mixture, mixing well.
Batter will be very thick.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and cut.

title: easy portuguese bean soup
directions: Put sausage, ham hocks, onion and water into large pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 1 hour.
Remove meat from ham hocks.
Put meat back into soup and add carrots, potatoes, cabbage and tomato sauce.
Cover and continue cooking for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Stir in undrained beans and cook a few more minutes, adding more water, if needed.
Serves 10 to 12.
Best if refrigerated overnight, skimming off excess grease before heating.

title: cranberry delight salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add cranberry sauce. Chill until slightly thickened; add remaining ingredients and refrigerate.
Can be served with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Also is attractive in ring mold with chicken or tuna salad in the center.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass pan. Layer ingredients in pan in order listed.
Do not stir.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: nachos
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place tortilla chips in a single layer on 2 baking sheets.
Sprinkle with jalapenos and green onions. Cover with shredded cheese.
Bake until cheese melts (about 5 minutes).
Serve warm from oven.
Serves 8 as an appetizer or 4 as a light lunch.

title: peppers stuffed with macaroni
directions: Cut a slice from top of each pepper and cook in boiling salted water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients, saving 1/3 of the cheese for topping.
Fill pepper with mixture, stand upright in pan and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pear honey
directions: Peel apples, pears, and orange.
Remove seeds.
Grind pears, apples, and orange.
Add sugar and cook 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add grated orange rind.
Cook until thick.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine 7 ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Spoon into a greased 3-quart baking dish. Top with mixture of cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour and salt.
Add oats, then shortening.
Mix vanilla and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and milk; beat on high for 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook onion in oleo until tender; add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sauteed alaska pollock
directions: Combine flour, garlic salt and pepper.
In separate dish, beat egg and water together.
Dip pollock in seasoned flour, then egg mixture, then in seasoned flour again.
Saute in oil over medium heat about 5 minutes or until lightly browned on both sides and pollock flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedge.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring rice and milk to boil; simmer for 40 minutes.
Beat eggs (by hand) and sugar together.
Add to rice and milk and cook until it boils again.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.

title: golden noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles.
Saute onions in butter.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix noodles with onion.
Mix in the rest of ingredients except bacon.
Put in casserole dish; bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with bacon on top.
Serves 4.

title: tuna pate(makes 3 cups)
directions: Blend together the first 4 ingredients.
Stir in tuna fish. Beat well to blend.
Pack in a 4-cup mold or round bowl.
Chill thoroughly.
Excellent on crackers or as a sandwich spread.

title: grandma lamantia's chicken
directions: Assemble chicken (skin side up or de-skinned side up) in ovenproof dish.
Pour lemon juice over chicken.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Put piece of butter on each piece.
Bake (covered) for 1 hour in 350° oven.
Uncover and bake for about 20 additional minutes.
(Salt and pepper may be added at this time or once cooking is complete.)

title: marinated venison pot roast
directions: Combine and bring to a boil wine vinegar, whole allspice, water, sugar, salt, onion and garlic.
Place roast in glass dish and pour combined ingredients over it.
Cover and leave overnight in marinade.
Dry roast off and roll in flour.
Brown on both sides.

title: hash browns
directions: Cook bacon and put aside.
Cut potatoes in small pieces and cut onions in small pieces.
Crumble bacon up and put in frypan. Stir for 3 to 4 minutes; add 1/2 cup water and cover for 20 minutes.

title: healthy hearty soup
directions: Brown meat, add onions and garlic, saute 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Add carrots, pinto beans, tomatoes (with liquid), beef broth, water, wine, bay leaf, salt, basil and pepper.
Heat to boil, cover and simmer 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add macaroni, cook 10 minutes.
Add green beans, cook 10 more minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: tangy green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Place separated onion rings over beans.
Fry bacon strips and save drippings.
Cut the strips in halves or quarters and lay over onion rings.
Sprinkle almonds over bacon.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; add enough water to juice to make 1 cup.
Heat to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in hot liquid.
Cool; gently stir in ginger ale.
Chill until partially set.
Blend pineapple and cranberry sauce; fold into gelatin.
Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Chill until firm.
Prepare topping per package directions.
Blend in cream cheese.
Spread on gelatin.
Toast pecans in 1 tablespoon butter in 350° oven 10 minutes.
Sprinkle over top and chill.

title: surprise cobbler
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Mix all ingredients except fruit.
Cook fruit 3 or 4 minutes and sweeten to taste.
Add first mixture to casserole dish, then add fruit.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 35 minutes.

title: kahlua
directions: Bring sugar and 2 cups water to a rolling boil.
Dissolve coffee in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to other ingredients.
Store 2 weeks in a dark place.

title: cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients together and press into cake pan or quiche pan.

title: nana's lasagne
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Serves 12.

title: fajitas of santa fe
directions: Combine chicken, onion, oil, lime juice, peppers, garlic and salsa in a sealed plastic bag.
Marinate in refrigerator 2 to 24 hours.

title: easy orange chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan; preheat oven to 350°.
Mix defrosted orange juice (without water) and package Lipton onion soup; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour or until brown, bubbly, done and delicious!

title: copper pennies
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over carrots, pepper and onion.
Toss together. Marinate overnight.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: In large bowl, crumble beef and heat 2 to 3 minutes on High until brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
In separate bowl, mix cottage cheese, egg and pepper together; set aside.
In oblong baking dish, spoon in 1/2 cup sauce.
Cover with layer of noodles, cheese and egg mixture, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses and sauce.
Top with 1 to 2 more layers.
Make sure all noodles are covered with sauce.
Cover with wax paper; heat on High 8 minutes.
Lower to Medium; cook for 30 more minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting to serve.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Slice one or two loaves angel food cake, depending on how much you want to make.
Layer one layer on bottom of dish (I use a large, oblong, plastic, deep dish).
Make 1 or 2 packages of French vanilla pudding as package directs.
Add a layer of the pudding over the cake.
Then add a layer of strawberries that have been washed, sliced and sweetened.
Then add a layer of Cool Whip. Can add another layer of each in the same order and slice a few strawberries on top of the last layer of Cool Whip. Keep refrigerated.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix ingredients (chocolate chips as desired) and pour into baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Clean
out
peppers.
In
a
small bowl, combine ground beef, onion, rice and salt.
Spoon into peppers.	Mix remaining
3 ingredients; pour over peppers.
Cook in slow cooker on low for 8 hours.

title: sherry's apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs and oil; beat until foamy.
Add sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix together well and add nuts. Mix well and add flour.
Mix well; add apples and put into a preheated 350° oven.
Start checking it at 50 minutes. Sometimes it needs to cook about 10 minutes more so put foil over the top so the crust doesn't get to brown.

title: leola's cabbage salad
directions: Mix cabbage and salt.
Let stand two hours. Boil sugar, vinegar and water, then let cool.
Mix celery, pepper, carrots, celery and mustard seed and add to other ingredients. Mix well. This freezes well.

title: mushroom pork chops casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Transfer to baking pan.
Surround with potatoes.
In bowl mix cream soup with water.
Pour mixture over pork chops and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Serve with favorite vegetable.

title: shrimp bites
directions: Stir all ingredients except muffins together.
Make sure it is mixed together well.
Slice all muffins open with a sharp knife to make smooth surface.
Spread the mixture on each half of the muffins, then cut each half into 8 pieces (like a pizza).
Place on cookie sheet and cook 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
These can be frozen.
Freeze them on a cookie sheet, then store them in plastic bags in the freezer.
Use as needed.
Keeps well frozen.
This recipe is great for appetizers.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Blend together in a blender.

title: fat rascals
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour 2 inches of oil in pan.
Drop batter by teaspoon.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes, until golden brown. Serve immediately.

title: apple crisp(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Place apples in 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Pour 1/3 cup of melted butter over top and dust with cinnamon.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and divide mixture in half.
Place half of mixture in baking pan, pressing flat with fingers.
Place on top of this mixture 1 cup sliced olives, 1 cup sliced mushrooms and any other pizza topping you like.
Sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Top this with other half of meat mixture, pressing it down over top of toppings.
Drizzle 1/2 cup pizza sauce over top. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Teens love it!

title: new potatoes in sour cream
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets in salted boiling water until tender; drain.
Chop onions very fine and cook in melted shortening until limp.
Stir in sugar, salt and flour and stir until smooth; gradually add sour cream and milk.
Pour in vinegar and continue to cook until mixture bubbles again.
Remove skins from potatoes; toss potatoes in sauce and keep hot until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Coat large skillet with vegetable cooking spray.
Saute onion and garlic over low heat until onion is tender.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook eggplant, covered, in small amount of boiling water for 3 to 5 minutes or until just tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain well. Combine Mozzarella and cottage cheese; set aside.

title: garden vegetable quiche
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onion, pepper, zucchini and mushrooms.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Add flour and tomato, stirring to completely blend in flour.
Beat together eggs, milk, seasoning salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle half the cheese in pie shell; add vegetables.
Pour egg-milk mixture over vegetables, then rest of the cheese. Garnish with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: quickie pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: mock red raspberry jam
directions: Put tomatoes through grinder and measure 2 cups.
Place in large pan.
Combine with sugar.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat, continue cooking 10 more minutes. Remove from heat; stir in jello and lemon juice until dissolved. Pour into jars; cover and cool.
Store in refrigerator or freezer. Makes about 6 jars.
Real good! Don't tell it's green tomatoes!

title: cheese balls
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Form into balls or rolls. Refrigerate for a few hours.
Serve.

title: glazed lamb loaf
directions: Combine egg, crumbs, salt, 1/3 of orange peel and pepper.
Add lamb; mix well.
Pat mixture in loaf pan.
Bake a 350° for 50 minutes.
Drain off fat.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream shortening and butter; add sugar, add eggs and beat well.
Add flour which has been stirred with salt and soda added. Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 350° about 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet to cool on rack.

title: cheez whiz potato casserole
directions: Boil 3 large potatoes until soft.
Drain and mash while hot. Add butter, salt, sour cream and Cheez Whiz. Whip until blended. Spray casserole dish with cooking spray and fill with potato mixture.

title: 2 flank steaks (marinated)
directions: Mix well.
Pierce meat with a fork on both sides.
Marinate meat 24 to 36 hours.
Grill to desired doneness.

title: pineapple filling for cake
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add pineapple and all of reserved juice except for 1/2 cup.
Cook until smooth and thickened.
Add orange juice.
When cool, spread between layers and top of cake. Frost cake with Seven Minute Icing.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat milk, eggs and peanut butter together; add gradually to dry ingredients.
Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Bring on the jelly!!)

title: hoe cakes
directions: Combine cornmeal and baking soda in medium bowl.
Add buttermilk, egg and 1 tablespoon melted shortening.
Stir just until mixture is moist.
Heat 1 tablespoon shortening on medium- high heat in heavy, large nonstick skillet.
Pour 1/4 cup of batter into skillet.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes, or until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels.

title: low-fat brown rice chicken bake
directions: Combine rice, peas, chicken, mayonnaise, almonds, soy sauce and seasonings in large bowl.
Transfer to a 3-quart baking dish coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: In blender, blend together well the onion, sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Slowly add oil while blending.
Add poppy seed and parsley.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Store in glass container.
Combine to taste with boiling water, 1 to 2 teaspoons per cup of hot water.

title: chili dip
directions: Smash the cream cheese on a microwave plate.
Cover cream cheese with the chili.
Top the chili with the shredded cheese. Cover and microwave for about 1 minute.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Put in a buttered baking dish.
Set in a pan of hot water. Bake at 325° until firm (about 45 minutes).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry (fruit) pizza
directions: Roll out sugar cookie dough onto an ungreased pizza pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Cool.
Mix vanilla, cream cheese and cool whip.
Spread on cooled cookie dough.
Mix strawberry glaze, strawberries, pineapple (add as much or as little as you prefer) and bananas.
Spread over cool whip mixture. You can garnish with frosting to look like cheese if you wish.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Begin melting margarine in a large saucepan. Add ketchup and then combine other ingredients as sauce simmers.
Stir in ingredients well and bring to a boil.
Let boil, while stirring constantly, for 3 to 4 minutes, then let stand for 30 minutes.

title: soft cheese ball
directions: Mix soft cream cheese with green onions.
Stir in one jar of dried beef mixed with Worcestershire sauce.
Form ball and roll in second jar of dried beef.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak to firm and slice diagonally across grain into very thin strips.
Combine cornstarch, sugar and ginger and stir in soy sauce.
Pour mixture over meat and stir.
Cut green peppers into strips and cut tomatoes into wedges.
Quickly brown beef strips (1/3 at a time) in hot oil and remove from pan. Reduce heat; add green peppers, garlic and water to pan and cook until tender-crisp 5 to 6 minutes.
Stir in meat and tomatoes and heat.
Serves 4.

title: hawaiian bread dip
directions: Soften onion with 1 tablespoon water in microwave for 15 seconds.
Combine all ingredients.
Let sit overnight.
Cut top off bread and hollow out most of the bread and cut into cubes to be used to dip.
Then put ingredients in hollowed out bread and place top back on.

title: grandma berry dumplins
directions: Mix flour with milk and form a tough dough.
Pinch off a biscuit size dough and roll flat.
Fill with berries of your choice.
Pinch dough together until tightly closed.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Then add other ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.
Let cool.
Then roll again.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Divide strawberries in half, putting the best ones in the bottom of pie shell.
Mash the rest of the berries and put in a saucepan.
Add sugar, cornstarch, salt and lemon juice.
Stir mixture constantly until thick.
Pour over berries in pie plate. Refrigerate until cool.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: spinach pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on flour tortillas. Roll each in jelly roll fashion and refrigerate for several hours. Slice into slices approximately 1-inch, using an electric knife.

title: mexican hot chocolate
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa powder, flour, cinnamon, and salt in a large saucepan.
Stir in cold water and bring to a boil stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring often.
Slowly stir in milk and heat almost to boiling.
Remove from heat, add vanilla. With a rotary beater or mixer, beat the mixture until it is frothy. Serve in mugs or cups garnishing each with a cinnamon stick or a dollop of whipped cream.
This is an unusual and delicious holiday drink.
Makes 10 servings.

title: chocolate bonbons
directions: Mix sugar, coconut, milk and vanilla.
Pour melted oleo over nuts, then add to first mixture. Chill dough.
Use melon baller to make bonbons for uniform size.
Melt chocolate chips and Parawax in double boiler. Dip each ball into chocolate and place on waxed paper.
Refrigerate or freeze.

title: orange dream
directions: Prepare jello according to package directions, replacing cold water with orange soda.
Mix in vanilla ice cream and refrigerate. Stir in about 1 hour and keep in refrigerator overnight. Mandarin oranges may be added when you add the ice cream.

title: pickle beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets into 1-quart bowl.
Set beets aside. To the liquid from beets, add equal amount of vinegar.
Microwave 5 to 7 minutes on High or until boiling.
Stir in sugar, salt, celery seed, cloves and cinnamon.
Microwave 1 minute on High or until sugar is dissolved.
Add beets.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours to blend flavors.

title: gourmet mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter and make paste with flour.
Heat chicken stock and gradually add to flour paste.
Add mushrooms to soup base with shallots or scallions.
Cook 7 minutes, stirring often.
Mix together heavy cream and egg yolks and gradually ladle soup into cream mixture until they fill a quart measure.
Gradually bring to a slow boil and boil a few minutes.
Pour a little Port wine or sherry into each serving, if desired.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on package except substitute pineapple juice for water.
Stir shredded coconut and rum flavoring into batter.
Pour batter into pans.
Bake as directed.
Cool cake.
Remove from pan and cool completely. Frost with whipped topping.
Sprinkle coconut on top if desired. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: crab cioppino
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 1 hour. Then add crab in the shell (optional: can add any white fish, shrimp or mussels).
Serve with sourdough bread.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Shell and devein shrimp.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Remove from heat; stir in flour and onion, blending until smooth.
Return to heat.
Add milk slowly.
Bring to boil, stirring until thickened.
Stir in coconut milk, salt, curry powder, ginger root, lemon juice and shrimp.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a medium bowl, combine pudding mix and milk and stir until mix is dissolved. Refrigerate 15 minutes, until partially set. Stir condensed milk into pudding mixture until smooth. Fold in sour cream and whipped topping. Fold in bananas. Make a single layer of vanilla wafers in bottom of a 9 x 13 inch dish. Spread pudding evenly over wafers.
Crush remaining wafers and sprinkle on top. Refrigerate until serving. Before serving, top each serving with Whipped Topping.

title: dirty rice
directions: Brown ground meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add Savoy dressing mix and rice.
Great side dish.

title: cathy's champagne punch
directions: Makes 1 punch bowl.
Chill before serving.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Melt chocolate with milk over low heat.
(Can also be melted in microwave.)
Remove from heat and stir in margarine, vanilla and sugar.
Be sure filling and icing are cool before spreading on cookies.

title: great grandma's egg nog
directions: Do half of eggs and half of cream at a time.
Beat 6 egg yolks 20 minutes.
Drop bourbon
in slowly as you beat.
In another bowl, beat 1 pint cream until stiff.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons of sugar. Add to yolks.
Beat 6 egg whites until no longer glossy (20 minutes).
Add 4 1/2 tablespoons sugar slowly.
Fold into egg yolks.
Repeat with second half of ingredients.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Thaw broccoli; add cheese to hot rice.
Stir broccoli in and Cheez Whiz.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: anzac biscuits("cookies")
directions: Combine oats, sugar, flour and butter together, then add golden syrup and lastly soda dissolved in the boiling water. Place spoonfuls of mixture onto a greased sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: microwave salsa dip
directions: Place softened cream cheese in quiche dish or glass pie plate. Spread evenly over bottom of dish.
Top with salsa and Jack cheese evenly.
Sprinkle scallions on top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Vent and microwave on High for 5 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn once.

title: blintze souffle
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with butter or cooking spray.
Line up blintzes in pan.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over blintzes.
Put all other ingredients in blender and blend until frothy.
Pour mixture over blintzes.
Bake 1 hour at 350° uncovered.

title: great grandmom mary's banana dessert
directions: Slice banana thinly, as for topping on cold cereal.
Sprinkle with sugar and, if desired, spice.
Serve in small bowl with spoon.
Cover banana with milk.
Yields about 2 servings.

title: beet-potato salad
directions: Place beets, potatoes, onions and celery in a large bowl.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard and sugar.
(If too thick, add a tablespoon of buttermilk to proper consistency.) Pour over seasoned vegetables; toss lightly but well.
Garnish with hard-cooked eggs and sprigs of parsley.
Chill well before serving.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Line bottom of pan with coconut and nuts.
Mix cake mix according to box directions and pour over coconut and nuts.
Melt butter and combine with confectioners sugar and cream cheese.
Mix well, then pour in lines into cake mix.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender; blend in flour and seasonings.
Stir in broth and cook until thick and bubbly.
Add vegetables and chicken.
Heat until bubbly.
Cool.
Put in casserole and top with pastry crust.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: pecan nougat
directions: Mix ingredients.
Add just enough unbeaten egg white to hold mixture together when pressed lightly with hand.
A teaspoon of mixture will make a nice-sized nougat.
The trick lies in the proper handling of the material.
Lightly mold into a roundish pat and bake until golden brown in a very slow oven.
Allow nougats to get cold before removing from baking sheets.
Delicious.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil in a heavy Dutch oven. Stir in grits. Return to boil. Reduce heat and cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in hominy, butter and cheese. Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chili
directions: Soak beans overnight. Cook in boiling salted water until tender. Drain. Brown onion, green pepper and meat in hot fat. Add tomatoes and seasonings. Simmer 2 hours, adding water if necessary. Add beans and heat thoroughly. Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Bake in greased pans at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: bob evans bread and sausage
directions: Saute onion and green pepper.
Cook sausage and drain good. Add sauteed onion and pepper.
Cut Velveeta into bite size pieces. Mix well with ingredients of sausage, onion and pepper (on low heat until cheese is melted).

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix everything but soda and boiling water.
Combine soda and water; add to batter.
Mix well.
Bake in a 325° oven in an 8 x 8-inch pan for 50 minutes.

title: chicken pecan pockets
directions: Mix together ingredients and serve in pita pockets.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles, then mix all ingredients together.
Cool and enjoy.

title: hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Pour in soups and water; stir thoroughly.
Mix with cooked noodles.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; whip in eggs and flour. Season.
Pour into greased casserole (2 quart).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: quick banana bread(yields 1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift before measuring flour.
Resift with baking powder.
Blend until creamy sugar and shortening.
Add in beaten egg and sliced bananas.
Add sifted ingredients in 3 parts.
Beat until smooth.
Place in greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: easy raspberry ice cream(makes 3 servings; carb count: 12 grams)
directions: Place raspberries in food processor fitted with steel blade. Process using on/off pulsing action about 15 seconds or until raspberries resemble coarse crumbs. Add sugar; process using on/off pulsing action until smooth. With processor running, add cream, processing until well blended.
Serve immediately.

title: rhubarb crumble
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Arrange rhubarb pieces in layers alternately with peel and 1 1/3 cups sugar.
In a bowl, combine the remaining ingredients for crumbs. Sprinkle over rhubarb.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Layer thinly sliced potatoes on bottom of pan.
Crumble part of hamburger meat over this, then salt and pepper.
Next make another layer of potatoes and then hamburger and salt and pepper. Pour soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce in saucepan and heat until mixes well.
Pour this over casserole and cover.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: spinach cheese bake
directions: Mix together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let sit 15 minutes to set.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Toss coconut flakes, chocolate bits and chopped pecans together.
Place in pie shell.
Mix sugars, salt and melted margarine. Beat in corn syrup and vanilla. Gently fold eggs into sugar mixture.
Pour evenly over ingredients in pie shell. Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until top is deep golden brown and nearly set in center.
Cool at room temperature.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Put oleo, buttermilk and cocoa on stove and stir until comes to a boil, then boil for 1 minute.
Add confectioners sugar.
Beat until smooth and spread on cake.

title: quiche
directions: ounce)
package frozen, chopped may be substituted for fresh.	Must be thawed and drained.

title: toasty nut granola
directions: Heat oats in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased baking pan in a preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: meatballs with pine nuts
directions: Mix all ingredients very thoroughly.
Form into meatballs a about the size of golf balls.
Drop into deep-fry oil one at a time and fry until golden brown.
Remove to paper toweling to drain. Serve with chili sauce or catsup.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on the box.
Pour into 13 x 9 inch pan.
Combine margarine and cream cheese in sauce pan. Heat on low until melted. Stir in box of confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake. Bake at 350° until cake is done.
Cake is upside down when turned out of pan onto plate.

title: chicken fettuccini
directions: Cook fettuccini according to package directions; drain and combine all ingredients in an ovenproof baking dish big enough to hold it all without bubbling over. Save about a fourth of the cheese and sprinkle it on top of the mixture. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, until it is hot and bubbly.

title: green chile sauce(for smothered burritos)
directions: Dredge pork in flour.
Brown in oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook until soft.
Add all other ingredients and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Remove cover the last 10 minutes to thicken.

title: strawberry pies(makes 2 pies)
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour into pie shells. Put in freezer overnight. Take out the next morning and put in regular fridge until ready to serve.

title: olive cheese balls
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Wrap a small amount around olive; form ball.
(May be frozen at this point until needed.) Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 50.

title: turkey vegetable chili(eat healthy)
directions: Cook bell peppers, onion and garlic in oil in a 3-quart pan over medium heat, stirring often, until onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except frozen vegetables and zucchini. Break up tomatoes.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in vegetables and zucchini.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes, until zucchini is crisp-tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue boats
directions: In skillet, cook onion and celery in butter until tender. Stir in catsup, water, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add the cut bologna strips into large skillet pan.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 15 minutes.
Put in a bun and enjoy.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over butter; pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips; press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Melt margarine; blend in flour and set aside.
Combine chicken cubes and water; heat.
Add milk, broccoli, soda and pepper and bring to boil.
Add milk mixture to flour, then put in milk mixture.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in cheese.

title: nacho chicken casserole
directions: Pour bag of chips into large casserole baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat soup, water or stock and margarine together.
Add rice, mushrooms, onion, celery, and pepper.
Mix well.
Stir in cheese and broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: wicklow pancake(traditional)
directions: Put a little of the shredded lettuce in the bottom of each stemmed glass.
Lay 6 prawns on top and mask with the following sauce:

title: millionaire fudge
directions: Put chocolate and hep-o lite in mixing bowl and set aside. In heavy skillet, bring butter, sugar and milk to boil and boil for 8 minutes or until soft ball.
Pour over chocolate mixture and let cool.
Mix in pecans and beat slightly.
Drop on wax paper.

title: gingerbread scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Measure milk in a glass cup measure; add molasses to the 2/3 cup mark and stir.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add butter and cut in with pastry blender until mixture looks like fine granules.
Stir milk mixture and add.
Stir with a fork to form a smooth, soft dough.
Turn out onto a floured surface, knead 10 to 12 times.
Cut dough into cubes or wedges and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on a wire rack.
Excellent served with honey, creme fraiche or cream cheese frosting.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil. When brown, remove and drain on paper towels.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook Karo, sugar and dash of salt over medium heat for 4 minutes.
Set off and cool.
Beat eggs and mix in, then the butter, pecans and vanilla.
Pour in pie shell and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg and applesauce.
Dust raisins with flour and add to the mixture.
Add ground cloves, cinnamon, allspice and soda to the flour and sift.
Add this to the creamy mixture.
Blend well.
Add vanilla and blend.
Put mixture in a greased Bundt cake pan.

title: marinated mushroom kabobs
directions: Drain mushrooms; place in a medium bowl. Prick tomatoes twice with a fork. Add to mushrooms along with olives. Add oil, vinegar, garlic powder, salt and pepper; mix well. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours. Thread a mushroom, tomato and olive on a toothpick or party pick. Repeat.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
In bowl, mix batter and pour over butter.
Top with fruit; do not stir.
Bake at 350° until batter is done, 30 minutes or more.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chill until firm (overnight).
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
This freezes well.

title: jean pierce's cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Whip or beat can of cranberry sauce and add to jello mixture.
Let cool.
Add pineapple, celery and nuts. Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish or square 9 x 9-inch dish. Refrigerate.
Keeps well.

title: strawberry tapioca salad
directions: In saucepan mix pudding, jello and water.
Heat until thick, stirring constantly.
When cool, add Cool Whip and fruit.
Cool.

title: chesapeake oysters rockefeller
directions: Arrange oysters in a single layer in greased shallow baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, except Parmesan cheese. Spread over oysters.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until top is hot and bubbly.

title: banana cake
directions: In first bowl, cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and mashed bananas.
Mix. In second bowl, mix together the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Alternately with milk and flour mixture into the first bowl, mixing while doing so.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 350° until fork comes out clean when placed in center of cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and zucchini.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients and add to wings.
Toss lightly.
Marinate at room temperature from 1 hour to overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour, basting every 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: baked graham cracker pie shell
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine crumbs with sugar and nutmeg; mix well.
With wooden spoon or fingers, rub in margarine until well blended.
Press mixture evenly on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Melt butter in saute pan; blanch garlic in melted butter until translucent.
Add tomato, green onion, red bell pepper, mushrooms and Worcestershire.
Spread mustard onto chicken breasts and add to saute pan; add half of the white wine.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn chicken; add remaining white wine; cover and cook another 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice with crabs
directions: Peel, core and coarsely chop tomato; set aside.
In skillet, cook rice and onion in hot oil over medium heat, stirring frequently, until rice is golden brown, 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water, jalapeno relish and Mexican rice seasoning mix.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Stir in peas; cook 5 minutes more.
Gently stir in crab or shrimp and tomato; heat through, 1 to 2 minutes more.
Makes 5 servings.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa together; add other ingredients.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and sausage
directions: Cut up chicken; cut sausage in about 2-inch links.
Cut potatoes in chunks; chop onion.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour can of tomato sauce and 1 can of water over this. Salt and pepper.
Add Italian seasoning.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: choralier's cornbread
directions: Sift flour, corn meal, sugar, salt, and baking powder together into a bowl.
Add eggs and shortening.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2 inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: cranberry apple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and let cool.
Stir in next seven ingredients and spoon into lightly oiled 5 cup mold.
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves and garnish with curls of orange rind.
Makes 8 servings.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with coloring and cocoa; add to mixture.
Add salt and flour with buttermilk and vanilla alternately.
Add soda and vinegar and do not beat hard, just blend.
Add butter flavoring.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees in two greased and floured 8 inch pans.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into fourths and shake into mixture of 3/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Put into well-greased Bundt cake pan.
