Melt on stove and pour over biscuits 3/4 cup butter, 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt.
Heat until sugar dissolves; let mixture cool.
Combine all other ingredients.
Pour sugar mixture over and marinate overnight.
Drain 2 hours before serving.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover with foil and bake 35 minutes or until firm.
Then sprinkle coconut over top.
(As the younger ones don't like coconut, sometimes I put marshmallows on their half.)
Cook about 10 more minutes at 375° until lightly browned.
Resembles sweet potato pie without the crust.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: In a medium saucepan, cover the potatoes with cold water, salt lightly and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and cook until tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain the potatoes, reserving about 3 tablespoons of cooking liquid.
Mash the potatoes with the reserved liquid until fluffy; fold in the Parmesan cheese and set aside.
Brown the meat in a frying pan, then transfer the cooked meat using a slotted spoon to a bowl; set aside.
Remove any fat from the frying pan.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Heat in skillet or wok.
Add shrimp (chicken, ham or beef may be used).
Season with salt, peppers and garlic powder; stir and brown.
Add egg and cook until it shreds.
Add rice and cook until brown.
Add soy sauce and sprinkle onions on top.
Serve immediately.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Punch holes into hot cake and pour can of Eagle Brand milk and caramel topping onto cake. Cover with pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cut in squares and put Cool Whip on top.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Drain liquid from grated cucumber.
Mix ingredients and use cucumber liquid to thin to a spreadable consistency.
Spread on bread, one white and one wheat or rye.

title: haman hats(jewish cookies)
directions: Mix well.
Put in refrigerator 1 hour.
Roll and cut into squares (1 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Spoon preserves (your choice) in center. Fold like 3 cornered hat (by pinching edges together). Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.
When cool, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: never fail ford biscuits
directions: Cut lard into flour sifted with soda, sugar and Bakewell cream.
Add milk.
Knead lightly.
Cut at least 1/2-inch thick. Bake in a 450° oven until browned or about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in unthawed strawberries. Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add crumbled pretzels and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Mix well.
Put evenly into pan to form a crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Combine sugar substitute and cornstarch in medium-size pan. Stir in grape juice and mashed peaches.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until mixture thickens, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Place sliced peaches in crunchy whole wheat pastry shell.
Spoon cooled peach mixture over sliced peaches.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 8 pieces.
Serves 8.

title: cran-berry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and pineapple with juice.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch container and let congeal.

title: chocolate-apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, blend all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until it tests done.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 425° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 375° and bake until knife is clean when tested.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add first 6 ingredients, simmer 15 minutes.
While meat mixture is cooking, prepare the other ingredients.
Cook egg noodles.
Mix green onion with cream cheese and sour cream. Grease a 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Put a layer of noodles, meat sauce, sour cream and cheese mixture.
Cover with sharp grated cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until good and hot at 350°.
This freezes well.
Mix the day before so the flavors can set.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil yams until tender.
Peel and slice yams.
Melt 1 stick butter in skillet.
Pour enough brown sugar in skillet to absorb butter and cook for a couple of minutes.
Add 1 tablespoon vanilla into mixture.
Add sliced yams and fry on both sides until coated with mixture.
Put in baking dish and bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.
If desired, marshmallows may be added to heated yams.
Put layer of marshmallows on top and place in broiler for about 2 minutes, until slightly browned.

title: prince of wales cake
directions: Note:
Don't sift except to mix flour and spices.

title: frozen heavenly salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with the juice from cherries.
Add powdered sugar and salad dressing.
Cream well. Add undrained crushed pineapple, slice cherries and Cool Whip.
May add other fruits, such as, mandarin oranges etc.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Mix and boil 1 minute the cocoa, sugar and milk.
Stir in margarine, peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper and let set until firm.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: cheddary pasta and vegetables
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, prepare macaroni according to package directions.
Add carrots, broccoli and pepper for last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In saucepan, combine remaining ingredients over low heat; melt cheese, stirring often.
Add macaroni and vegetables.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Serves 5.

title: chicken a la forestiere
directions: Halve each chicken filet and dust with seasoned flour.
Melt butter or margarine in a skillet and lightly brown chicken.
Add bacon and onion; saute until brown.
Add wine, water, mushrooms and potatoes.
Mix gently, cover and cook on low heat until potatoes are done.
Adjust seasoning, if necessary, and sprinkle with parsley.
Serves four.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix well; use little hands if necessary or willing.
Roll into balls.
Can be used as edible play dough.
Makes about 15 small balls.

title: german chocolate cake frosting
directions: Cream the margarine. Stir in the evaporated milk, sugar and egg yolks.
Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and coconut. Beat until thick.
Add nuts and smooth over cake.

title: arroz con gandules(rice with pigeon peas)
directions: Drain cooked beans and set aside, but reserve 3 cups cooking liquid.
Wash rice under cold running water and drain.
Heat oil in a heavy kettle or Dutch oven.
Brown salt pork.
Add onion and bell pepper and saute for 3 minutes.
Stir in the rice.
Add beans and reserve liquid.
Mix and add salt, pepper and oregano.
Boil, uncovered, on moderate heat until water is absorbed and rice is dry (about 4 to 5 minutes).
Cover and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.
Turn off heat and let the rice sit for 10 minutes before serving.

title: deep dish brownies
directions: Blend melted butter, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs; beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; add to egg mixture.
Mix well.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Put water, onion, chicken, parsley and bouillon cubes in a large saucepan or Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Drop in frozen noodles; stir to separate.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Makes 8 one-cup servings.

title: pork roast
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour this over a pork loin roast. Bake for 4 hours at 350°, covered.
Do not lift lid.

title: church window candy
directions: Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Add chocolate chips and stir until dissolved.
When mixture is cool, add vanilla.
Combine the marshmallows and pecans to mixture.
Pour out on sugared wax paper and form into 2 logs.
Store in refrigerator to firm.
Slice into desired thickness.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Add the first 3 ingredients in a mixing bowl. Set aside until the butter melts into the cake pan. Pour the batter into the butter. Put the peaches on top. Bake in oven at 350° until golden brown.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together and form in small biscuits.
Bake at 350°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix shredded cabbage and carrots.
Add just enough Miracle Whip to moisten.
Add salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Onion may also be added, if you like it.

title: green velvet salad
directions: Add enough water to reserved pineapple juice to make 1 1/2 cups; heat and dissolve jello and cream cheese.
Add other ingredients; fold in whipping cream last.
May be placed in a mold and refrigerated.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Fill skillet with apples.
Add the butter, sugar, and cinnamon to the apples, stirring to mix well.
Cook until apples are soft.
Let cool a bit.

title: sauteed liver with bacon
directions: Coat liver lightly with flour.
Saute over medium-high heat until lightly browned.
Do not overcook.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve with hot, crisp bacon.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine and pour in a buttered dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: quick coconut cream pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in half of Cool Whip and half of coconut.
Pour into crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pie. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Chill.

title: brownies
directions: Take 16 pieces of chocolate; put in the refrigerator for 100 minutes.
Cut and eat.

title: holiday brussels sprouts
directions: In large
saucepan,
bring
water to boil, add bouillon cube and
stir
to dissolve.
Add Brussels sprouts, cook until done. Add
onion
and
pepper the last few minutes of cooking time. Drain, keep warm.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk. Stir in hot mashed potatoes, shortening, sugar and salt. Let stand until lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast over warm water in large mixing bowl. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in potato-milk mixture. Beat eggs thoroughly and add to mixture with 1 1/2 cups of flour. Beat well and cover.
Let stand in warm place about 1 hour. Stir in remaining flour. Knead.
Put in a greased mixing bowl.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 hours.
Make into cloverleaf rolls in greased muffin tins and let stand until double in size. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli-water chestnut casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on package.
In greased baking dish, layer broccoli, water chestnuts, soup and cheese. Crush cracker crumbs and put on top.
(I drizzle a little melted margarine over the crumbs.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: company breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain on paper towel. Place bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, butter side up. Mix eggs, sour cream and milk. Spread sausage over bread. Pour egg mixture over sausage. Top with cheese. Cover and store in refrigerator 12 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
Serves 12.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions on package.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done; cool in pan.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water; let cool.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken until well done.
Chop onion, bell pepper and cheese.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix all together.
Reserve the broth.

title: potato salad
directions: In medium saucepan, combine milk, sugar, vinegar, egg, butter, cornstarch, salt, celery seed and dry mustard.
Cook and stir over low heat until thickened.
Remove from heat; blend in onions and mayonnaise and let cool.
Combine potatoes and hard-cooked eggs. Carefully fold in dressing.
Chill.
Before serving, sprinkle with paprika.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix together sour cream, soup and dill weed. Add green onions, black olives, Cheddar cheese and shrimp. Mix with cooked noodles. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and chopped chives. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: In 4-quart microproof mixing bowl combine chocolate, butterscotch and butter.
Cook on 70 (Roast) 5 minutes or until melted.
Stir.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Spread on buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set (about 2 hours). Cut into squares.

title: sauce bechamel
directions: Basic Cream Sauce:
This white sauce may be made with half chicken stock and half cream or with milk.
It is a fine dressing for egg dishes, vegetables, fish, grains or pastas.
Melt butter in small saucepan over moderate heat.
Add flour; blend well, then slowly stir in the milk.
Cook, stirring, until the mixture thickens and is smooth.
Add salt, pepper and scraped onion or onion juice.
Some cooks like to add a little chopped parsley or chives.
A half teaspoon of Worcestershire sauce or a little nutmeg is also good.

title: toffee
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In heavy 3-quart saucepan, stir together sugar, corn syrup and cream.

Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 260° or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a ball which is hard enough to hold its shape, yet elastic.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Continue stirring 2 minutes.
Turn into prepared pan.
Cool slightly.

title: lasagna
directions: In hot oil, brown garlic and ground beef.
Stir in soup mix, water, tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, sugar and oregano.
Cover and cook 30 minutes.
Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs, flour and milk.
Add nuts, coconut, dates and candy.
Beat well.
Bake 2 hours at 250° in tube pan.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: Chop 1/2 pound mushrooms. Slice remaining 1/2 pound and set aside.
In a kettle, melt 4 tablespoons butter.
Add the chopped mushrooms along with onion and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes.
Stir in broth, water, tomato paste, salt, black pepper and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in barley.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add parsley, celery and carrots.
Cook, covered, about 30 minutes longer or until vegetables and barley are tender.
In medium skillet, melt remaining 2 tablespoons butter. Add the reserved sliced mushrooms and saute 5 minutes.
Add to soup along with sherry.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: doritos chicken
directions: Boil chicken; bone and chop.
Mix soups and picante sauce.
Add to chicken and mix well.
In a large casserole dish, place a layer of Doritos, a layer of chicken mixture, a layer of grated cheese and then Doritos.
Continue, ending with a topping of Doritos. Place in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes to melt cheese.

title: deerburger casserole
directions: In a deep frying pan, saute onion, bell pepper and celery in small amount of vegetable oil until tender.

Add meat and cook on top of stove until redness is gone. Stir frequently until well mixed. Add tomatoes, water, rice, salt, pepper and tomato sauce. Mix well and let simmer with lid on until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° until light brown. Sprinkle with cheese.
Run back into oven about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: shrimp in clam sauce
directions: In large skillet, heat olive oil until hot.
Add shrimp and saute until shrimp turn opaque.
Don't overcook.
Add white clam sauce, oregano and lemon juice.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over shrimp. Cook over high heat, basting shrimp with sauce until sauce is slightly thickened, about one minute.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes.
Add margarine, eggs and sugar.
Blend together good and add vanilla and milk.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples as usual for pie.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Pour over apples and mix.
Put in crust.
Add 1 or 2 envelopes of Sweet 'N Low, if desired.

title: frozen jam
directions: Mix berries and sugar well.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Bring Sure-Gel and water to a boil; stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute. Pour into berries; stir for 2 minutes.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Steam rice in broth for 1 minute.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken or turkey on top (cooked).
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cover pan with foil; it will make the dressing more moist.
If you don't have chicken broth, water will do.

title: cauliflower bacon salad
directions: Mix dressing, cheese, sugar and onion in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Sprinkle sugar over apples.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until brown.

title: corn mazatlan
directions: Drain corn, reserving 3 tablespoons liquid.
Combine reserved liquid and cream cheese in saucepan.
Heat and blend until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook for 15 minutes over low heat.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream together and add pretzels, press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Let stand in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight. Next day, roll out and cut into biscuits.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: beef steak provencale
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper. Sprinkle 1 side of beef steak with half of the flour mixture. Pound in. Turn beef and pound in remaining flour mixture.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs.
Blend raw zucchini until smooth and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla. Sift dry ingredients, then beat into creamed mixture until smooth. Add nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Stir in eggs, milk and butter; mix well. Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole dish or use cooking spray. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: fresh vegetable soup
directions: Use
fresh
vegetables;
cook each vegetable separately until done.
Then combine and simmer for about 1 hour.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large kettle or Dutch oven.
Add onions and garlic; saute 5 minutes.
Add the ground beef; cook until brown, breaking the meat up with a fork until it cooks.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Bring the mixture to a simmer, then cook over low heat until it is thick and rich, 45 minutes to an hour. Remove the bay leaves; skim off the fat.
This makes about 10 cups, plenty for 2 hearty family dishes.
It freezes well.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in boiling water.
Dissolve jello in 12 cups boiling water.
Combine sugar and jello mixture and add to this orange juice, lemon juice and pineapple juice.
When ready to serve add ginger ale.
Makes approximately 3 gallons.
Serves 100.
Can be frozen.
If frozen, remove from freezer about 5 or 6 hours before serving.

title: rabbit benelux style
directions: Place rabbit pieces overnight in a marinade made of the ale, Worcestershire, garlic, bay leaves, spices, onion and carrot.

title: a. j.'s jam cake
directions: Blend all the ingredients together, mixing well.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 3 layer round pans (butter and flour pans).

title: easy hamburger quiche
directions: Brown meat over medium heat. Drain well. Blend mayonnaise, milk, eggs and cornstarch until smooth. Stir in meat, cheese, onions and pepper.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown on top.
Knife inserted in center should come out clean.

title: trifle
directions: Cut pound cake crosswise and fill with jam.
Put into bowl and sprinkle with sherry.
Cover cake with a layer of fruit, then layer of pudding, alternating layers.
Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook and stir over hot, not boiling, water until thick.
Cool.
Stir in fruits and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spoon gently into serving bowl; chill 24 hours.
Trim with orange sections and green seedless grapes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and celery in oleo.
Add soups and cheese. Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Fold in broccoli and rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put into greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fondant
directions: Mix well and separate into desired sections.
Add a flavoring (peppermint, maple, cinnamon, etc.) to each section and form into small balls.
Cool in refrigerator while making chocolate coating. Spear small ball with toothpick and dip into chocolate. Immediately lay aside to cool.

title: *apple torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add egg and beat well.
Add apples and nuts.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 9 to 14.

title: monkey cake
directions: Butter tube pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together in small bowl.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Roll in sugar mixture and put in tube pan.
Melt margarine and brown sugar together. Pour over biscuits in pan.
Bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove from oven and immediately invert onto large plate and remove pan.
Cool.
Ready to pull off pieces and eat.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar; cut in Crisco with fork. Add buttermilk.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: lipton cheese ball
directions: Mix first four ingredients until well blended.
Use round bottom bowl.
Cut dried beef in small pieces.
Line bowl with beef.
Put cheese mix onto top.
Sprinkle remaining beef on top. Turn out on wax paper to shape.
Chill and serve with crackers. Mixture is easier to work with if refrigerated.

title: six cup salad
directions: Mix all together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes at 450° for 45 minutes or until done. Allow potatoes to cool. When cool, slice skin away from top of each potato. Carefully scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact. Mash pulp and add the above ingredients, mixing well with an electric mixer. Stuff shells with potato mixture. You may freeze the potatoes at this point. Before you serve the potatoes, bake another 15 minutes at 450°. This works well when you have leftover baked potatoes.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: Cook noodles in salted water until tender.
Drain and rinse. Combine spinach, cream cheese, onions, Parmesan cheese, pepper, garlic, eggs and cheese in a mixer.
Beat well.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix in blender until frothy.

title: judy's chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk; beat 1 minute.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers (whole).
Spread half of filling.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Place remaining filling on top and then another layer of crackers.
Gently spread top with frosting.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Makes 16 servings.

title: hamburg casserole no. 1
directions: Press raw hamburger in casserole pan.
Place sliced onion over hamburger.
Place sliced potatoes over onions.
Place sliced carrots over potatoes.
Pour soup over all.
Add grated cheese on top of all this.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours covered, then uncover and brown, about 1/2 hour.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Cook ground beef and onion, drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, mushrooms, parsley, salt, pepper & oregano.
Unroll one package of rolls and separate into triangles.
Place in a lightly greased 9 pie plate, pressing edges together to form a pie shell. Separate one of the eggs, set yolk aside.
Beat egg white with the remaining 2 eggs.
Pour half the beaten eggs over pie shell.
Spoon meat mixture into shell.
Arrange cheese slices on top - spread with remaining beaten eggs.

title: parm-a-chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese, flour and seasoning.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk.
Coat with cheese mixture. Place in baking pan and pour margarine over chicken.
Bake 1 hour. Serve with additional cheese.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: ladosh
directions: Marinate the meat in all the ingredients for 1 hour. Transfer meat to a pot. Add 1/2 cup water (or more, depending on type of meat.)
Cover and boil over low heat until meat is tender and most of the water has evaporated.
Take off heat and set aside.

title: pumpkin bread in jars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix eggs, pumpkin and water until smooth.
Add flour, soda and spices; stir in nuts.
Grease wide mouth pint jars.
Fill jars half full of batter.
Bake in oven at 325° for 45 minutes.
When done, remove one jar at a time, cleaning around top, putting on lids to seal.
Make sure to tighten lids. Makes 8 pints.
Will keep all year.
Squash or sweet potatoes can be used in place of pumpkin.

title: squash rotel
directions: Saute squash and onion in butter.
Add milk, tomatoes, salt, pepper and cheese.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: super cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Shred Jack and Cheddar together in large bowl.
Add mayonnaise until spreading consistency is reached.
Flavor with garlic.
Bake on cookie sheet until cheese is melted.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Roll into balls and press flat with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 375°.

title: spaghetti dinner
directions: Boil spaghetti according to directions on box.
drain liquid and rinse with cold water.
Add sauce and cheese.
(I spray my 10 x 13 inch pyrex dish with vegetable spray to avoid hard crust build up.)
Lay strips of bacon on top of spaghetti.
Bake at 350 to 375° 40 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: instant mocha
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Use 3 teaspoons to 6 ounces hot water.

title: french onion soup
directions: Peel and slice onions thin.
Melt butter or margarine in saucepan. Saute onion until lightly browned.
Add beef stock and seasonings.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add parsley and cheese.
Pour into bowls.
Top with small slices of toast sprinkled with cheese.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Coat a 6-cup Bundt pan with vegetable cooking spray; dust with 1 tablespoon flour and set aside.

title: tossed salad
directions: Wash greens and break into pieces.
Cut up onion into rings and cut up tomatoes.
Toss with greens. Mix oil, vinegar, garlic, salt and pepper. Shake dressing well.

title: chicken enchilada pie
directions: Cook and bone chicken.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Reserve 1 cup broth.
Combine soups, green chilies, chili powder, broth, onion, garlic powder, salt and pepper and blend well.
Cover bottom of 3-quart casserole with 2 cups of chips.
Layer half of chicken over chips, half the sauce, then half of grated cheese. Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken with onion and celery until done.
Dice chicken into small pieces.
Mix in large bowl the dressing mix, mushroom soup, milk, eggs, broth, butter and chicken.
Mix well.
Pour in baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh red raspberry cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl. Add sugar, shortening and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes more.
Fold in raspberries. Put into two greased and floured 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° until it springs back when dented with a finger.
Sweetened whipped cream with more raspberries folded in makes an excellent frosting.

title: rich white cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy; gradually add sugar and cream until light.
Sift the flour; measure and sift with baking powder.
Add the flour alternately with the liquid and add extracts.
Beat smooth between each addition.
Whip the egg whites until just stiff, but not dry and carefully fold them in.
Bake in 2 layers or sheet cake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: low fat oven fries
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

title: chicken polo
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In bag, combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and seasonings.
Place chicken (one at a time) in bag and shake to coat.
Arrange chicken in a single layer in a small shallow roasting dish.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes, basting occasionally.
Pour sherry or extra broth over chicken and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda, and salt, set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter and shortening on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugars and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop from a teaspoon 2 inches apart onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in a pre-heated oven at 375° for 8 - 10 minutes or until golden in color.
Remove; cool.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Beat all together; add nuts and rind.
Use long narrow loaf pan; line pan with waxed paper.
Bake for 1 hour at 300°.
Cool slightly for 5 or 10 minutes.
Pour over while in pan, 1/3 cup sugar mixed with juice of 1 lemon.
If regular bread pan is used, bake at 300° for 3/4 hour and 10 or 15 minutes at 350°.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in sherbet.
Let set a few minutes.
Add fruit.
Pour into mold or dish and place in refrigerator.

title: corn and ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles, brown meat and onions, pour into 2 large pans and mix in remaining ingredients except cheese.
(Can be refrigerated at this point until the next day, if desired.)
Top with the grated cheese and bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 50.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch strips.
Brown meat in butter in large Dutch oven.
Add onion soup mix, mushroom soup and 2 cups water. Cook 45 minutes.
Add rice and 2 cups water.
Cook until water is absorbed.
Add sour cream before serving.

title: kettle ham
directions: Put ham in Dutch oven or other kettle with a tight lid.
Boil for 45 minutes.
Then add other ingredients.
Bring back to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Allow to stand and steep several hours or overnight before serving.

title: hot tamales
directions: Crumble raw ground beef well; mix together the next 7 ingredients well.
Then mix into the ground beef.
Add the water and mix well.
Form into cylinder shapes approximately 5 to 6 inches long and about as big around as your thumb.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream sweet potato and butter and cool. Sift dry ingredients into potato.
Stir in enough milk to make a dough you can handle.
Put dough on floured board.
Shape into a ball and pat or roll and cut out biscuits.
Arrange on greased pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes or until brown.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients. Work in butter. Add milk gradually. Put on floured board. Pat and roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut in strips or drop by spoonfuls on top of meat and broth. Cook until done.

title: saucy zucchini
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in boiling water until tender. In a saucepan melt butter, blend in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk all at once. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Combine sauce with cooked vegetables. Place in a baking dish. Top with shredded cheese and then buttered crumbs. Bake in 350°F oven for 25 minutes.

title: lime jello
directions: Bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Remove from fire and add the jello and mix until thoroughly dissolved.
Cool until it starts to set.
Then add the buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Stir until thoroughly mixed. Put into a 9 x 11-inch pan and refrigerate.
Can use other flavors of jello if desired.

title: banana luncheon bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add mashed banana and mix well.
Blend in flour mixture. Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool before slicing.

title: fruit float
directions: Melt margarine in a long or square Pyrex dish (1 1/2-quart size); sift the flour together with the sugar and spices.
Add milk and stir until smooth.
Pour into melted butter in Pyrex dish, but do not stir.
Distribute the fruit over top of butter; do not stir.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: pineapple cream cheese pie
directions: Thoroughly drain crushed pineapple; add softened cream cheese, milk and other ingredients.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and pecans last.
Fill pie shells and refrigerate.

title: vanilla cappuccino
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk and vanilla.
Scald the milk. Remove from the heat.
Cover and let milk steep for 5 minutes.
If you like your coffee sweetened, stir sugar into milk.
Reheat milk briefly over high heat until steaming.
Remove the vanilla bean. Transfer milk to blender.
Whirl milk until frothy (45 seconds). Half fill 2 warmed coffee mugs with hot coffee.
Add the hot milk, dividing it evenly.
Sprinkle the cinnamon lightly on top.

title: hot lettuce dressing
directions: Wash and drain lettuce.
Fry chipped bacon on low heat.
Beat together eggs, mayo and sugar.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and water to mixture.
Mix well and pour in a frypan along with bacon and bacon grease.
Stir over low heat until sauce thickens.
Set aside until cool enough to pour over lettuce.

title: mexican dip
directions: Line dish with ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes and serve with chips.

title: eisenhower delight
directions: Place layer of cracker crumbs on bottom of baking dish, the 1 cup of white sauce. Layer cheese, pimentos and eggs. Repeat. Top with bread crumbs.

title: herb-baked tomatoes
directions: Coat a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Arrange tomatoes in dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well.
Sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes at 425° or until tomatoes are thoroughly heated and topping is lightly browned.
Serve hot.
Serves 6. Contains 39 calories per serving.

title: eggs scrambled with cream cheese
directions: Melt in double boiler over simmering water the cream cheese and butter.
Scald and stir in cream.
Add salt and paprika. Break the eggs into the sauce.
Before the egg whites are firm, stir the eggs gently with a fork until thick.
Add sherry.
Yields 4 servings.

title: chicken mandarin salad
directions: Empty chicken broth in large pan and bring to a boil.
Add macaroni and cook until done.
Drain macaroni and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.

title: til's marinara sauce
directions: Saute all but last 3 ingredients.
Then add tomato paste, water and tomatoes.
Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Lower heat to low, boil for 4 to 6 hours.
Let mixture cook down and become thick.

title: sausage bread
directions: Mix egg, garlic salt and pepper.
Thaw bread dough at a time you can begin work on the dough as soon as thawed.
Fry sausage (two loaves of sausage bread are made from 1 1/2 pounds sausage). Drain off all grease and finely crumble.
Butter hands and spread bread dough out into a uniform (as possible) large rectangular shape.
Spread with mix with brush or hands on inside of bread dough.
Place crumbled sausage evenly down middle of rectangle. Sprinkle cheese down middle of rectangle on top of sausage (use 4 ounce minimum of cheese per loaf).
Carefully roll dough, using long side of rectangle into a loaf.
Pinch ends together.
It will be very big.

title: easy breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage.
Mix eggs; add them to sausage.
Add cheese, salt and pepper.
Place mixture into shells.
Bake 10 minutes until warm.

title: lemon or chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in oblong 9 x 9 x 18-inch baking dish.
Bake 18 minutes at 350°. Cool.
Beat until smooth the cream cheese, half container Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread atop cooled flour mixture.
Mix together pudding and milk.
Spread on top of cream cheese.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top of lemon pudding.
If desired, sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Keep refrigerated.

title: italian beef(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Combine all into crock-pot.
Cook
on low for 8 to 10 hours. Meat will fall apart.

title: pork tenderloin with spiced chutney
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in large Dutch oven.
Bring to a simmer, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Then add rest of ingredients. Cook until rhubarb is tender and mixture thickens slightly (about 5 minutes).

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Combine oleo and sugar; add egg and then dry ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven until done.
Roll dough into balls and press flat on cookie sheet with the palm of your hand.
(To prevent dough from sticking to the hand, make mixture of sugar and cinnamon and press hand on mixture before flattening dough.)

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Put sugar, Crisco and eggs in a big bowl and beat very well. Add remaining ingredients to first mixture and mix well.
Put in greased angel food pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Bake 2 layers of the cake mix as directed.
(You can make 4 layers by pulling thru each layer with sewing thread.)

title: hawaiian paradise salad
directions: Mix ingredients together lightly. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Drain pineapple.
Chop the green peppers and onions fine.
Mix all ingredients, saving 1 cup pecans.
Chill for 1 hour or unti firm.
Form into ball and roll in last cup of pecans.

title: low-fat pasta salad
directions: Slice cucumbers, quarter tomatoes and slice onions.
Add oregano, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Let set a few hours. Right before serving, drain off water and mix with mayonnaise.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, mustard, onion, lemon juice, cayenne pepper and salt. Drain shrimp and cut into small pieces and stir into cheese mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Form into 3 1/2 dozen 1/2-inch balls or one large cheese round.
Roll in nuts. Serve chilled or bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Blend cream cheese with sugar thoroughly.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Line sides and bottom of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Spoon half the mixture.
Top with pie filling. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix dry pudding and pineapple.
Add marshmallows and nuts. Mix in Cool Whip, then chill for 2 or 3 hours.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Sift in flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a rectangular pan.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
Add onions and peppers; cook. Stir in chopped can of tomatoes and can of pizza sauce from box of pizza.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Prepare dough per directions on pizza box.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Press dough into bottom and halfway up sides.
Layer; cover dough with 1 package of Mozzarella cheese, then 1/2 of meat sauce.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese from pizza box.
More cheese may be added. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: cheese potatoes(serves 4)
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with butter, salt, pepper and parsley.
Put cheese over potatoes and add cream. Bake one hour at 400° or 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: crab bites
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, garlic salt, seasoned salt and crab meat.
Spread mixture on muffin halves.
Bake 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Cut each half into 8 wedges.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes and Parmesan cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Spread in ungreased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch) or 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, if desired. Cover and cook in a 325° oven for 1 hour.
Uncover and cook until potatoes are tender, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: coconut butter balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend flour (sifted) and salt; stir into creamed mixture, blending thoroughly.
If dough is soft, chill until firm enough to shape.
With fingers, shape a rounded teaspoonful of dough around each pecan half (cut very large pecan halves in two) to form 1-inch balls.
Beat egg white and water with fork.
Dip dough in egg white mixture, then in coconut.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: sour cream potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes whole; do not overcook. Cool and grate coarsely. Melt oleo and grated cheese; stir in sour cream.
Dot top with oleo. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
